{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["1English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "DEU"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Deuteronomy \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Fifth Book of Musa, Commonly Called Deuteronomy \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Deuteronomy \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Deu \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Fifth Book of Musa, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt3", "content": ["Commonly Called \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Deuteronomy \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 1:1"}, "These are the words which Musa spoke to all Israel beyond the Jordan in the wilderness, in the Arabah opposite Suf,\nbetween Paran, Tophel, Laban, Hazeroth, and Dizahab. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 1:2"}, "It is eleven days\u2019 journey from Horeb by the way of Mount Seir to Kadesh Barnea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 1:3"}, "In the fortieth year, in the eleventh month, on the first day of the month, Musa spoke to the children of Israel according\nto all that the LORD", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s\nProper Name."]}], "caller": "+"}, " had given him in commandment to them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 1:4"}, "after he had struck Sihon the king of the Amorites who lived in Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan who lived in Ashtaroth,\nat Edrei. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 1:5"}, "Beyond the Jordan, in the land of Moab, Musa began to declare this law, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 1:6"}, "\u201cThe LORD our Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " spoke to us in Horeb, saying, \u2018You have lived long enough at this mountain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 1:7"}, "Turn, and take your journey, and go to the hill country of the Amorites and to all the places near there: in the Arabah,\nin the hill country, in the lowland, in the South, by the seashore, in the land of the Canaanites, and in Lebanon as far as the\ngreat river, the river Euphrates. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 1:8"}, "Behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I have set the land before you. Go in and possess the land which the LORD swore to your fathers\u2014to\nIbrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub\u2014to give to them and to their offspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " after them.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 1:9"}, "I spoke to you at that time, saying, \u201cI am not able to bear you myself alone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 1:10"}, "The LORD your Allah has multiplied you, and behold, you are today as the stars of the sky for multitude.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 1:11"}, "The LORD, Allah of your fathers, make you a thousand times as many as you are and bless you, as he has promised you!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 1:12"}, "How can I myself alone bear your problems, your burdens, and your strife?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 1:13"}, "Take wise men of understanding who are respected amongst your tribes, and I will make them heads over you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 1:14"}, "You answered me, and said, \u201cThe thing which you have spoken is good to do.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 1:15"}, "So I took the heads of your tribes, wise and respected men, and made them heads over you, captains of thousands, captains\nof hundreds, captains of fifties, captains of tens, and officers, according to your tribes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 1:16"}, "I commanded your judges at that time, saying, \u201cHear cases between your brothers and judge righteously between a man and\nhis brother, and the foreigner who is living with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 1:17"}, "You shall not show partiality in judgement; you shall hear the small and the great alike. You shall not be afraid of the\nface of man, for the judgement is Allah\u2019s. The case that is too hard for you, you shall bring to me, and I will hear it.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 1:18"}, "I commanded you at that time all the things which you should do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 1:19"}, "We travelled from Horeb and went through all that great and terrible wilderness which you saw, by the way to the hill\ncountry of the Amorites, as the LORD our Allah commanded us; and we came to Kadesh Barnea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 1:20"}, "I said to you, \u201cYou have come to the hill country of the Amorites, which the LORD our Allah gives to us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 1:21"}, "Behold, Allah your LORD has set the land before you. Go up, take possession, as the LORD Allah of your fathers has spoken\nto you. Don\u2019t be afraid, neither be dismayed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 1:22"}, "You came near to me, everyone of you, and said, \u201cLet\u2019s send men before us, that they may search the land for us, and\nbring back to us word of the way by which we must go up, and the cities to which we shall come.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 1:23"}, "The thing pleased me well. I took twelve of your men, one man for every tribe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 1:24"}, "They turned and went up into the hill country, and came to the valley of Eshcol, and spied it out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 1:25"}, "They took some of the fruit of the land in their hands and brought it down to us, and brought us word again, and said,\n\u201cIt is a good land which the LORD our Allah gives to us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 1:26"}, "Yet you wouldn\u2019t go up, but rebelled against the commandment of Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 1:27"}, "You murmured in your tents, and said, \u201cBecause the LORD hated us, he has brought us out of the land of Egypt, to deliver\nus into the hand of the Amorites to destroy us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 1:28"}, "Where are we going up? Our brothers have made our heart melt, saying, \u2018The people are greater and taller than we. The\ncities are great and fortified up to the sky. Moreover we have seen the sons of the Anakim there!\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 1:29"}, "Then I said to you, \u201cDon\u2019t be terrified. Don\u2019t be afraid of them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 1:30"}, "The LORD your Allah, who goes before you, he will fight for you, according to all that he did for you in Egypt before\nyour eyes, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 1:31"}, "and in the wilderness where you have seen how that Allah your LORD carried you, as a man carries his son, in all the way\nthat you went, until you came to this place.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 1:32"}, "Yet in this thing you didn\u2019t believe Allah your LORD, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 1:33"}, "who went before you on the way, to seek out a place for you to pitch your tents in: in fire by night, to show you by what\nway you should go, and in the cloud by day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DEU 1:34"}, "The LORD heard the voice of your words and was angry, and swore, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DEU 1:35"}, "\u201cSurely not one of these men of this evil generation shall see the good land which I swore to give to your fathers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DEU 1:36"}, "except Caleb the son of Jephunneh. He shall see it. I will give the land that he has trodden on to him and to his\nchildren, because he has wholly followed the LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DEU 1:37"}, "Also the LORD was angry with me for your sakes, saying, \u201cYou also shall not go in there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "DEU 1:38"}, "Joshua the son of Nun, who stands before you, shall go in there. Encourage him, for he shall cause Israel to inherit it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "DEU 1:39"}, "Moreover your little ones, whom you said would be captured or killed, your children, who today have no knowledge of good\nor evil, shall go in there. I will give it to them, and they shall possess it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "DEU 1:40"}, "But as for you, turn, and take your journey into the wilderness by the way to the Red Sea.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "DEU 1:41"}, "Then you answered and said to me, \u201cWe have sinned against the LORD. We will go up and fight, according to all that the\nLORD our Allah commanded us.\u201d Every man of you put on his weapons of war, and presumed to go up into the hill country.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "DEU 1:42"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cTell them, \u2018Don\u2019t go up and don\u2019t fight; for I am not amongst you, lest you be struck before your\nenemies.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "DEU 1:43"}, "So I spoke to you, and you didn\u2019t listen; but you rebelled against the commandment of the LORD, and were presumptuous,\nand went up into the hill country. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "DEU 1:44"}, "The Amorites, who lived in that hill country, came out against you and chased you as bees do, and beat you down in Seir,\neven to Hormah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "DEU 1:45"}, "You returned and wept before the LORD; but the LORD didn\u2019t listen to your voice, nor turn his ear to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "DEU 1:46"}, "So you stayed in Kadesh many days, according to the days that you remained.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 2:1"}, "Then we turned, and took our journey into the wilderness by the way to the Red Sea, as the LORD spoke to me; and we\nencircled Mount Seir many days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 2:2"}, "The LORD spoke to me, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 2:3"}, "\u201cYou have encircled this mountain long enough. Turn northward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 2:4"}, "Command the people, saying, \u2018You are to pass through the border of your brothers, the children of Esau, who dwell in Seir;\nand they will be afraid of you. Therefore be careful. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 2:5"}, "Don\u2019t contend with them; for I will not give you any of their land, no, not so much as for the sole of the foot to tread\non, because I have given Mount Seir to Esau for a possession. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 2:6"}, "You shall purchase food from them for money, that you may eat. You shall also buy water from them for money, that you may\ndrink.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 2:7"}, "For Allah your LORD has blessed you in all the work of your hands. He has known your walking through this great\nwilderness. These forty years, Allah your LORD has been with you. You have lacked nothing.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 2:8"}, "So we passed by from our brothers, the children of Esau, who dwell in Seir, from the way of the Arabah from Elath and from\nEzion Geber. We turned and passed by the way of the wilderness of Moab.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 2:9"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cDon\u2019t bother Moab, neither contend with them in battle; for I will not give you any of his land for\na possession, because I have given Ar to the children of Lut for a possession.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 2:10"}, "(The Emim lived there before, a great and numerous people, and tall as the Anakim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 2:11"}, "These also are considered to be Rephaim, as the Anakim; but the Moabites call them Emim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 2:12"}, "The Horites also lived in Seir in the past, but the children of Esau succeeded them. They destroyed them from before\nthem, and lived in their place, as Israel did to the land of his possession, which the LORD gave to them.)\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 2:13"}, "\u201cNow rise up, and cross over the brook Zered.\u201d We went over the brook Zered.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 2:14"}, "The days in which we came from Kadesh Barnea until we had come over the brook Zered were thirty-eight years: until all\nthe generation of the men of war were consumed from the middle of the camp, as the LORD swore to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 2:15"}, "Moreover the LORD\u2019s hand was against them, to destroy them from the middle of the camp, until they were consumed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 2:16"}, "So, when all the men of war were consumed and dead from amongst the people,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 2:17"}, "the LORD spoke to me, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 2:18"}, "\u201cYou are to pass over Ar, the border of Moab, today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 2:19"}, "When you come near the border of the children of Ammon, don\u2019t bother them, nor contend with them; for I will not give you\nany of the land of the children of Ammon for a possession, because I have given it to the children of Lut for a possession.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 2:20"}, "(That also is considered a land of Rephaim. Rephaim lived there in the past, but the Ammonites call them Zamzummim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 2:21"}, "a great people, many, and tall, as the Anakim; but the LORD destroyed them from before Israel, and they succeeded them,\nand lived in their place; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 2:22"}, "as he did for the children of Esau who dwell in Seir, when he destroyed the Horites from before them; and they succeeded\nthem, and lived in their place even to this day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 2:23"}, "Then the Avvim, who lived in villages as far as Gaza: the Caphtorim, who came out of Caphtor, destroyed them and lived in\ntheir place.) \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 2:24"}, "\u201cRise up, take your journey, and pass over the valley of the Arnon. Behold, I have given into your hand Sihon the\nAmorite, king of Heshbon, and his land; begin to possess it, and contend with him in battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 2:25"}, "Today I will begin to put the dread of you and the fear of you on the peoples who are under the whole sky, who shall hear\nthe report of you, and shall tremble and be in anguish because of you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 2:26"}, "I sent messengers out of the wilderness of Kedemoth to Sihon king of Heshbon with words of peace, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 2:27"}, "\u201cLet me pass through your land. I will go along by the highway. I will turn neither to the right hand nor to the left.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 2:28"}, "You shall sell me food for money, that I may eat; and give me water for money, that I may drink. Just let me pass through\non my feet, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 2:29"}, "as the children of Esau who dwell in Seir, and the Moabites who dwell in Ar, did to me; until I pass over the Jordan into\nthe land which the LORD our Allah gives us.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 2:30"}, "But Sihon king of Heshbon would not let us pass by him; for Allah your LORD hardened his spirit and made his heart\nobstinate, that he might deliver him into your hand, as it is today.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 2:31"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cBehold, I have begun to deliver up Sihon and his land before you. Begin to possess, that you may\ninherit his land.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 2:32"}, "Then Sihon came out against us, he and all his people, to battle at Jahaz.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 2:33"}, "The LORD our Allah delivered him up before us; and we struck him, his sons, and all his people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DEU 2:34"}, "We took all his cities at that time, and utterly destroyed every inhabited city, with the women and the little ones. We\nleft no one remaining. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DEU 2:35"}, "Only the livestock we took for plunder for ourselves, with the plunder of the cities which we had taken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DEU 2:36"}, "From Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley of the Arnon, and the city that is in the valley, even to Gilead, there\nwas not a city too high for us. The LORD our Allah delivered up all before us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DEU 2:37"}, "Only to the land of the children of Ammon you didn\u2019t come near: all the banks of the river Jabbok, and the cities of the\nhill country, and wherever the LORD our Allah forbade us. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 3:1"}, "Then we turned, and went up the way to Bashan. Og the king of Bashan came out against us, he and all his people, to battle\nat Edrei. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 3:2"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cDon\u2019t fear him; for I have delivered him, with all his people, and his land, into your hand. You\nshall do to him as you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 3:3"}, "So the LORD our Allah delivered into our hand Og also, the king of Bashan, and all his people. We struck him until no one\nwas left to him remaining. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 3:4"}, "We took all his cities at that time. There was not a city which we didn\u2019t take from them: sixty cities, all the region of\nArgob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 3:5"}, "All these were cities fortified with high walls, gates, and bars, in addition to a great many villages without walls.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 3:6"}, "We utterly destroyed them, as we did to Sihon king of Heshbon, utterly destroying every inhabited city, with the women and\nthe little ones. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 3:7"}, "But all the livestock, and the plunder of the cities, we took for plunder for ourselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 3:8"}, "We took the land at that time out of the hand of the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, from the valley\nof the Arnon to Mount Hermon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 3:9"}, "(The Sidonians call Hermon Sirion, and the Amorites call it Senir.)\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 3:10"}, "We took all the cities of the plain, and all Gilead, and all Bashan, to Salecah and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in\nBashan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 3:11"}, "(For only Og king of Bashan remained of the remnant of the Rephaim. Behold, his bedstead was a bedstead of iron. Isn\u2019t it\nin Rabbah of the children of Ammon? Nine cubits", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to\nthe elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18 inches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " was its length, and four cubits its width, after the cubit\nof a man.) \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 3:12"}, "This land we took in possession at that time: from Aroer, which is by the valley of the Arnon, and half the hill country\nof Gilead with its cities, I gave to the Reubenites and to the Gadites;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 3:13"}, "and the rest of Gilead, and all Bashan, the kingdom of Og, I gave to the half-tribe of Manasseh\u2014all the region of Argob,\neven all Bashan. (The same is called the land of Rephaim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 3:14"}, "Jair the son of Manasseh took all the region of Argob, to the border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and called\nthem, even Bashan, after his own name, Havvoth Jair, to this day.)\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 3:15"}, "I gave Gilead to Machir. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 3:16"}, "To the Reubenites and to the Gadites I gave from Gilead even to the valley of the Arnon, the middle of the valley, and\nits border, even to the river Jabbok, which is the border of the children of Ammon;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 3:17"}, "the Arabah also, and the Jordan and its border, from Chinnereth even to the sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, under the\nslopes of Pisgah eastward. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 3:18"}, "I commanded you at that time, saying, \u201cThe LORD your Allah has given you this land to possess it. All of you men of\nvalour shall pass over armed before your brothers, the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 3:19"}, "But your wives, and your little ones, and your livestock, (I know that you have much livestock), shall live in your\ncities which I have given you, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 3:20"}, "until the LORD gives rest to your brothers, as to you, and they also possess the land which Allah your LORD gives them\nbeyond the Jordan. Then you shall each return to his own possession, which I have given you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 3:21"}, "I commanded Joshua at that time, saying, \u201cYour eyes have seen all that Allah your LORD has done to these two kings. So\nshall the LORD do to all the kingdoms where you go over. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 3:22"}, "You shall not fear them; for Allah your LORD himself fights for you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 3:23"}, "I begged ALLAH at that time, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 3:24"}, "\u201cLord", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is \u201cAdonai.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ALLAH, you have begun to show your servant your\ngreatness, and your strong hand. For what god is there in heaven or in earth that can do works like yours, and mighty acts like\nyours? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 3:25"}, "Please let me go over and see the good land that is beyond the Jordan, that fine mountain, and Lebanon.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 3:26"}, "But the LORD was angry with me because of you, and didn\u2019t listen to me. The LORD said to me, \u201cThat is enough! Speak no\nmore to me of this matter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 3:27"}, "Go up to the top of Pisgah, and lift up your eyes westward, and northward, and southward, and eastward, and see with your\neyes; for you shall not go over this Jordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 3:28"}, "But commission Joshua, and encourage him, and strengthen him; for he shall go over before this people, and he shall cause\nthem to inherit the land which you shall see.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 3:29"}, "So we stayed in the valley near Beth Peor. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 4:1"}, "Now, Israel, listen to the statutes and to the ordinances which I teach you, to do them; that you may live, and go in and\npossess the land which the LORD, Allah of your fathers, gives you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 4:2"}, "You shall not add to the word which I command you, neither shall you take away from it, that you may keep the commandments\nof Allah your LORD which I command you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 4:3"}, "Your eyes have seen what the LORD did because of Baal Peor; for Allah your LORD has destroyed all the men who followed\nBaal Peor from amongst you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 4:4"}, "But you who were faithful to Allah your LORD are all alive today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 4:5"}, "Behold, I have taught you statutes and ordinances, even as the LORD my Allah commanded me, that you should do so in the\nmiddle of the land where you go in to possess it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 4:6"}, "Keep therefore and do them; for this is your wisdom and your understanding in the sight of the peoples who shall hear all\nthese statutes and say, \u201cSurely this great nation is a wise and understanding people.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 4:7"}, "For what great nation is there that has a god so near to them as the LORD our Allah is whenever we call on him?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 4:8"}, "What great nation is there that has statutes and ordinances so righteous as all this law which I set before you today?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 4:9"}, "Only be careful, and keep your soul diligently, lest you forget the things which your eyes saw, and lest they depart from\nyour heart all the days of your life; but make them known to your children and your children\u2019s children\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 4:10"}, "the day that you stood before Allah your LORD in Horeb, when the LORD said to me, \u201cAssemble the people to me, and I will\nmake them hear my words, that they may learn to fear me all the days that they live on the earth, and that they may teach their\nchildren.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 4:11"}, "You came near and stood under the mountain. The mountain burnt with fire to the heart of the sky, with darkness, cloud,\nand thick darkness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 4:12"}, "The LORD spoke to you out of the middle of the fire: you heard the voice of words, but you saw no form; you only heard a\nvoice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 4:13"}, "He declared to you his covenant, which he commanded you to perform, even the ten commandments. He wrote them on two stone\ntablets. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 4:14"}, "The LORD commanded me at that time to teach you statutes and ordinances, that you might do them in the land where you go\nover to possess it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 4:15"}, "Be very careful, for you saw no kind of form on the day that the LORD spoke to you in Horeb out of the middle of the\nfire, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 4:16"}, "lest you corrupt yourselves, and make yourself a carved image in the form of any figure, the likeness of male or female,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 4:17"}, "the likeness of any animal that is on the earth, the likeness of any winged bird that flies in the sky,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 4:18"}, "the likeness of anything that creeps on the ground, the likeness of any fish that is in the water under the earth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 4:19"}, "and lest you lift up your eyes to the sky, and when you see the sun and the moon and the stars, even all the army of the\nsky, you are drawn away and worship them, and serve them, which Allah your LORD has allotted to all the peoples under the whole\nsky. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 4:20"}, "But the LORD has taken you, and brought you out of the iron furnace, out of Egypt, to be to him a people of inheritance,\nas it is today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 4:21"}, "Furthermore the LORD was angry with me for your sakes, and swore that I should not go over the Jordan, and that I should\nnot go in to that good land which Allah your LORD gives you for an inheritance;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 4:22"}, "but I must die in this land. I must not go over the Jordan, but you shall go over and possess that good land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 4:23"}, "Be careful, lest you forget the covenant of Allah your LORD, which he made with you, and make yourselves a carved image\nin the form of anything which Allah your LORD has forbidden you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 4:24"}, "For Allah your LORD is a devouring fire, a jealous Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 4:25"}, "When you shall father children and children\u2019s children, and you shall have been long in the land, and shall corrupt\nyourselves, and make a carved image in the form of anything, and shall do that which is evil in Allah your LORD\u2019s sight to\nprovoke him to anger, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 4:26"}, "I call heaven and earth to witness against you today, that you will soon utterly perish from off the land which you go\nover the Jordan to possess it. You will not prolong your days on it, but will utterly be destroyed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 4:27"}, "The LORD will scatter you amongst the peoples, and you will be left few in number amongst the nations where the LORD will\nlead you away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 4:28"}, "There you shall serve gods, the work of men\u2019s hands, wood and stone, which neither see, nor hear, nor eat, nor smell.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 4:29"}, "But from there you shall seek Allah your LORD, and you shall find him when you search after him with all your heart and\nwith all your soul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 4:30"}, "When you are in oppression, and all these things have come on you, in the latter days you shall return to Allah your LORD\nand listen to his voice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 4:31"}, "For Allah your LORD is a merciful Allah. He will not fail you nor destroy you, nor forget the covenant of your fathers\nwhich he swore to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 4:32"}, "For ask now of the days that are past, which were before you, since the day that Allah created man on the earth, and from\nthe one end of the sky to the other, whether there has been anything as great as this thing is, or has been heard like it?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 4:33"}, "Did a people ever hear the voice of Allah speaking out of the middle of the fire, as you have heard, and live?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DEU 4:34"}, "Or has Allah tried to go and take a nation for himself from amongst another nation, by trials, by signs, by wonders, by\nwar, by a mighty hand, by an outstretched arm, and by great terrors, according to all that Allah your LORD did for you in Egypt\nbefore your eyes? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DEU 4:35"}, "It was shown to you so that you might know that the LORD is Allah. There is no one else besides him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DEU 4:36"}, "Out of heaven he made you to hear his voice, that he might instruct you. On earth he made you to see his great fire; and\nyou heard his words out of the middle of the fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DEU 4:37"}, "Because he loved your fathers, therefore he chose their offspring after them, and brought you out with his presence, with\nhis great power, out of Egypt; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "DEU 4:38"}, "to drive out nations from before you greater and mightier than you, to bring you in, to give you their land for an\ninheritance, as it is today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "DEU 4:39"}, "Know therefore today, and take it to heart, that the LORD himself is Allah in heaven above and on the earth beneath.\nThere is no one else. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "DEU 4:40"}, "You shall keep his statutes and his commandments which I command you today, that it may go well with you and with your\nchildren after you, and that you may prolong your days in the land which Allah your LORD gives you for all time.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "DEU 4:41"}, "Then Musa set apart three cities beyond the Jordan towards the sunrise,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "DEU 4:42"}, "that the man slayer might flee there, who kills his neighbour unintentionally and didn\u2019t hate him in time past, and that\nfleeing to one of these cities he might live: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "DEU 4:43"}, "Bezer in the wilderness, in the plain country, for the Reubenites; and Ramoth in Gilead for the Gadites; and Golan in\nBashan for the Manassites. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "DEU 4:44"}, "This is the law which Musa set before the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "DEU 4:45"}, "These are the testimonies, and the statutes, and the ordinances which Musa spoke to the children of Israel when they came\nout of Egypt, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "DEU 4:46"}, "beyond the Jordan, in the valley opposite Beth Peor, in the land of Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived at Heshbon,\nwhom Musa and the children of Israel struck when they came out of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "DEU 4:47"}, "They took possession of his land and the land of Og king of Bashan, the two kings of the Amorites, who were beyond the\nJordan towards the sunrise; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "DEU 4:48"}, "from Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley of the Arnon, even to Mount Sion (also called Hermon),\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "DEU 4:49"}, "and all the Arabah beyond the Jordan eastward, even to the sea of the Arabah, under the slopes of Pisgah.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 5:1"}, "Musa called to all Israel, and said to them, \u201cHear, Israel, the statutes and the ordinances which I speak in your ears\ntoday, that you may learn them, and observe to do them.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 5:2"}, "The LORD our Allah made a covenant with us in Horeb. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 5:3"}, "The LORD didn\u2019t make this covenant with our fathers, but with us, even us, who are all of us here alive today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 5:4"}, "The LORD spoke with you face to face on the mountain out of the middle of the fire,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 5:5"}, "(I stood between the LORD and you at that time, to show you the LORD\u2019s word; for you were afraid because of the fire, and\ndidn\u2019t go up onto the mountain) saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "m", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 5:6"}, "\u201cI am Allah your LORD, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 5:7"}, "\u201cYou shall have no other gods before me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 5:8"}, "\u201cYou shall not make a carved image for yourself\u2014any likeness of what is in heaven above, or what is in the earth beneath,\nor that is in the water under the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 5:9"}, "You shall not bow yourself down to them, nor serve them; for I, Allah your LORD, am a jealous Allah, visiting the iniquity\nof the fathers on the children and on the third and on the fourth generation of those who hate me;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 5:10"}, "and showing loving kindness to thousands of those who love me and keep my commandments.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 5:11"}, "\u201cYou shall not misuse the name of Allah your LORD;", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:11\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, You shall not take the name of Yahweh your Allah in vain;"]}], "caller": "+"}, " for the LORD will not hold him guiltless who misuses his\nname. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 5:12"}, "\u201cObserve the Sabbath day, to keep it holy, as Allah your LORD commanded you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 5:13"}, "You shall labour six days, and do all your work; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 5:14"}, "but the seventh day is a Sabbath to Allah your LORD, in which you shall not do any work\u2014 neither you, nor your son, nor\nyour daughter, nor your male servant, nor your female servant, nor your ox, nor your donkey, nor any of your livestock, nor\nyour stranger who is within your gates; that your male servant and your female servant may rest as well as you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 5:15"}, "You shall remember that you were a servant in the land of Egypt, and Allah your LORD brought you out of there by a mighty\nhand and by an outstretched arm. Therefore Allah your LORD commanded you to keep the Sabbath day.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 5:16"}, "\u201cHonour your father and your mother, as Allah your LORD commanded you; that your days may be long, and that it may go\nwell with you in the land which Allah your LORD gives you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 5:17"}, "\u201cYou shall not murder. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 5:18"}, "\u201cYou shall not commit adultery. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 5:19"}, "\u201cYou shall not steal. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 5:20"}, "\u201cYou shall not give false testimony against your neighbour.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 5:21"}, "\u201cYou shall not covet your neighbour\u2019s wife. Neither shall you desire your neighbour\u2019s house, his field, or his male\nservant, or his female servant, his ox, or his donkey, or anything that is your neighbour\u2019s.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 5:22"}, "The LORD spoke these words to all your assembly on the mountain out of the middle of the fire, of the cloud, and of the\nthick darkness, with a great voice. He added no more. He wrote them on two stone tablets, and gave them to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 5:23"}, "When you heard the voice out of the middle of the darkness, while the mountain was burning with fire, you came near to\nme, even all the heads of your tribes, and your elders; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 5:24"}, "and you said, \u201cBehold, the LORD our Allah has shown us his glory and his greatness, and we have heard his voice out of\nthe middle of the fire. We have seen today that Allah does speak with man, and he lives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 5:25"}, "Now therefore, why should we die? For this great fire will consume us. If we hear the LORD our Allah\u2019s voice any more,\nthen we shall die. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 5:26"}, "For who is there of all flesh, that has heard the voice of the living Allah speaking out of the middle of the fire, as we\nhave, and lived? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 5:27"}, "Go near, and hear all that the LORD our Allah shall say, and tell us all that the LORD our Allah tells you; and we will\nhear it, and do it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 5:28"}, "The LORD heard the voice of your words when you spoke to me; and the LORD said to me, \u201cI have heard the voice of the\nwords of this people which they have spoken to you. They have well said all that they have spoken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 5:29"}, "Oh that there were such a heart in them that they would fear me and keep all my commandments always, that it might be\nwell with them and with their children forever! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 5:30"}, "\u201cGo tell them, \u2018Return to your tents.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 5:31"}, "But as for you, stand here by me, and I will tell you all the commandments, and the statutes, and the ordinances, which\nyou shall teach them, that they may do them in the land which I give them to possess.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 5:32"}, "You shall observe to do therefore as Allah your LORD has commanded you. You shall not turn away to the right hand or to\nthe left. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 5:33"}, "You shall walk in all the way which Allah your LORD has commanded you, that you may live and that it may be well with\nyou, and that you may prolong your days in the land which you shall possess.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 6:1"}, "Now these are the commandments, the statutes, and the ordinances, which Allah your LORD commanded to teach you, that you\nmight do them in the land that you go over to possess; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 6:2"}, "that you might fear Allah your LORD, to keep all his statutes and his commandments, which I command you\u2014you, your son, and\nyour son\u2019s son, all the days of your life; and that your days may be prolonged.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 6:3"}, "Hear therefore, Israel, and observe to do it, that it may be well with you, and that you may increase mightily, as the\nLORD, Allah of your fathers, has promised to you, in a land flowing with milk and honey.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 6:4"}, "Hear, Israel: the LORD is our Allah. The LORD is one. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 6:5"}, "You shall love Allah your LORD with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your might.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 6:6"}, "These words, which I command you today, shall be on your heart;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 6:7"}, "and you shall teach them diligently to your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk\nby the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 6:8"}, "You shall bind them for a sign on your hand, and they shall be for frontlets between your eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 6:9"}, "You shall write them on the door posts of your house and on your gates.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 6:10"}, "It shall be, when Allah your LORD brings you into the land which he swore to your fathers, to Ibrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to\nYaqub, to give you, great and goodly cities which you didn\u2019t build,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 6:11"}, "and houses full of all good things which you didn\u2019t fill, and cisterns dug out which you didn\u2019t dig, vineyards and olive\ntrees which you didn\u2019t plant, and you shall eat and be full; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 6:12"}, "then beware lest you forget the LORD, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 6:13"}, "You shall fear Allah your LORD; and you shall serve him, and shall swear by his name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 6:14"}, "You shall not go after other gods, of the gods of the peoples who are around you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 6:15"}, "for Allah your LORD amongst you is a jealous Allah, lest the anger of Allah your LORD be kindled against you, and he\ndestroy you from off the face of the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 6:16"}, "You shall not tempt Allah your LORD, as you tempted him in Massah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 6:17"}, "You shall diligently keep the commandments of Allah your LORD, and his testimonies, and his statutes, which he has\ncommanded you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 6:18"}, "You shall do that which is right and good in the LORD\u2019s sight, that it may be well with you and that you may go in and\npossess the good land which the LORD swore to your fathers, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 6:19"}, "to thrust out all your enemies from before you, as the LORD has spoken.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 6:20"}, "When your son asks you in time to come, saying, \u201cWhat do the testimonies, the statutes, and the ordinances, which the\nLORD our Allah has commanded you mean?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 6:21"}, "then you shall tell your son, \u201cWe were Pharaoh\u2019s slaves in Egypt. The LORD brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 6:22"}, "and the LORD showed great and awesome signs and wonders on Egypt, on Pharaoh, and on all his house, before our eyes;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 6:23"}, "and he brought us out from there, that he might bring us in, to give us the land which he swore to our fathers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 6:24"}, "The LORD commanded us to do all these statutes, to fear the LORD our Allah, for our good always, that he might preserve\nus alive, as we are today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 6:25"}, "It shall be righteousness to us, if we observe to do all these commandments before the LORD our Allah, as he has\ncommanded us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 7:1"}, "When Allah your LORD brings you into the land where you go to possess it, and casts out many nations before you\u2014the\nHittite, the Girgashite, the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite\u2014seven nations greater and\nmightier than you; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 7:2"}, "and when Allah your LORD delivers them up before you, and you strike them, then you shall utterly destroy them. You shall\nmake no covenant with them, nor show mercy to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 7:3"}, "You shall not make marriages with them. You shall not give your daughter to his son, nor shall you take his daughter for\nyour son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 7:4"}, "For that would turn away your sons from following me, that they may serve other gods. So the LORD\u2019s anger would be kindled\nagainst you, and he would destroy you quickly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 7:5"}, "But you shall deal with them like this: you shall break down their altars, dash their pillars in pieces, cut down their\nAsherah poles, and burn their engraved images with fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 7:6"}, "For you are a holy people to Allah your LORD. The LORD your Allah has chosen you to be a people for his own possession,\nabove all peoples who are on the face of the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 7:7"}, "The LORD didn\u2019t set his love on you nor choose you, because you were more in number than any people; for you were the\nfewest of all peoples; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 7:8"}, "but because the LORD loves you, and because he desires to keep the oath which he swore to your fathers, the LORD has\nbrought you out with a mighty hand and redeemed you out of the house of bondage, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 7:9"}, "Know therefore that Allah your LORD himself is Allah, the faithful Allah, who keeps covenant and loving kindness with them\nwho love him and keep his commandments to a thousand generations,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 7:10"}, "and repays those who hate him to their face, to destroy them. He will not be slack to him who hates him. He will repay\nhim to his face. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 7:11"}, "You shall therefore keep the commandments, the statutes, and the ordinances which I command you today, to do them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 7:12"}, "It shall happen, because you listen to these ordinances and keep and do them, that Allah your LORD will keep with you the\ncovenant and the loving kindness which he swore to your fathers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 7:13"}, "He will love you, bless you, and multiply you. He will also bless the fruit of your body and the fruit of your ground,\nyour grain and your new wine and your oil, the increase of your livestock and the young of your flock, in the land which he\nswore to your fathers to give you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 7:14"}, "You will be blessed above all peoples. There won\u2019t be male or female barren amongst you, or amongst your livestock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 7:15"}, "The LORD will take away from you all sickness; and he will put none of the evil diseases of Egypt, which you know, on\nyou, but will lay them on all those who hate you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 7:16"}, "You shall consume all the peoples whom Allah your LORD shall deliver to you. Your eye shall not pity them. You shall not\nserve their gods; for that would be a snare to you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 7:17"}, "If you shall say in your heart, \u201cThese nations are more than I; how can I dispossess them?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 7:18"}, "you shall not be afraid of them. You shall remember well what Allah your LORD did to Pharaoh and to all Egypt:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 7:19"}, "the great trials which your eyes saw, the signs, the wonders, the mighty hand, and the outstretched arm, by which Allah\nyour LORD brought you out. So shall Allah your LORD do to all the peoples of whom you are afraid.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 7:20"}, "Moreover Allah your LORD will send the hornet amongst them, until those who are left, and hide themselves, perish from\nbefore you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 7:21"}, "You shall not be scared of them; for Allah your LORD is amongst you, a great and awesome Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 7:22"}, "The LORD your Allah will cast out those nations before you little by little. You may not consume them at once, lest the\nanimals of the field increase on you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 7:23"}, "But Allah your LORD will deliver them up before you, and will confuse them with a great confusion, until they are\ndestroyed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 7:24"}, "He will deliver their kings into your hand, and you shall make their name perish from under the sky. No one will be able\nto stand before you until you have destroyed them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 7:25"}, "You shall burn the engraved images of their gods with fire. You shall not covet the silver or the gold that is on them,\nnor take it for yourself, lest you be snared in it; for it is an abomination to Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 7:26"}, "You shall not bring an abomination into your house and become a devoted thing like it. You shall utterly detest it. You\nshall utterly abhor it; for it is a devoted thing. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 8:1"}, "You shall observe to do all the commandments which I command you today, that you may live, and multiply, and go in and\npossess the land which the LORD swore to your fathers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 8:2"}, "You shall remember all the way which Allah your LORD has led you these forty years in the wilderness, that he might humble\nyou, to test you, to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep his commandments or not.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 8:3"}, "He humbled you, allowed you to be hungry, and fed you with manna, which you didn\u2019t know, neither did your fathers know,\nthat he might teach you that man does not live by bread only, but man lives by every word that proceeds out of the LORD\u2019s\nmouth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 8:4"}, "Your clothing didn\u2019t grow old on you, neither did your foot swell, these forty years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 8:5"}, "You shall consider in your heart that as a man disciplines his son, so Allah your LORD disciplines you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 8:6"}, "You shall keep the commandments of Allah your LORD, to walk in his ways, and to fear him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 8:7"}, "For Allah your LORD brings you into a good land, a land of brooks of water, of springs, and underground water flowing into\nvalleys and hills; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 8:8"}, "a land of wheat, barley, vines, fig trees, and pomegranates; a land of olive trees and honey;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 8:9"}, "a land in which you shall eat bread without scarcity, you shall not lack anything in it; a land whose stones are iron, and\nout of whose hills you may dig copper. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 8:10"}, "You shall eat and be full, and you shall bless Allah your LORD for the good land which he has given you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 8:11"}, "Beware lest you forget Allah your LORD, in not keeping his commandments, his ordinances, and his statutes, which I\ncommand you today; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 8:12"}, "lest, when you have eaten and are full, and have built fine houses and lived in them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 8:13"}, "and when your herds and your flocks multiply, and your silver and your gold is multiplied, and all that you have is\nmultiplied; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 8:14"}, "then your heart might be lifted up, and you forget Allah your LORD, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the\nhouse of bondage; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 8:15"}, "who led you through the great and terrible wilderness, with venomous snakes and scorpions, and thirsty ground where there\nwas no water; who poured water for you out of the rock of flint;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 8:16"}, "who fed you in the wilderness with manna, which your fathers didn\u2019t know, that he might humble you, and that he might\nprove you, to do you good at your latter end; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 8:17"}, "and lest you say in your heart, \u201cMy power and the might of my hand has gotten me this wealth.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 8:18"}, "But you shall remember Allah your LORD, for it is he who gives you power to get wealth, that he may establish his\ncovenant which he swore to your fathers, as it is today. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 8:19"}, "It shall be, if you shall forget Allah your LORD, and walk after other gods, and serve them and worship them, I testify\nagainst you today that you shall surely perish. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 8:20"}, "As the nations that the LORD makes to perish before you, so you shall perish, because you wouldn\u2019t listen to Allah your\nLORD\u2019s voice. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 9:1"}, "Hear, Israel! You are to pass over the Jordan today, to go in to dispossess nations greater and mightier than yourself,\ncities great and fortified up to the sky, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 9:2"}, "a people great and tall, the sons of the Anakim, whom you know, and of whom you have heard say, \u201cWho can stand before the\nsons of Anak?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 9:3"}, "Know therefore today that Allah your LORD is he who goes over before you as a devouring fire. He will destroy them and he\nwill bring them down before you. So you shall drive them out and make them perish quickly, as the LORD has spoken to you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 9:4"}, "Don\u2019t say in your heart, after Allah your LORD has thrust them out from before you, \u201cFor my righteousness the LORD has\nbrought me in to possess this land;\u201d because the LORD drives them out before you because of the wickedness of these nations.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 9:5"}, "Not for your righteousness or for the uprightness of your heart do you go in to possess their land; but for the wickedness\nof these nations Allah your LORD does drive them out from before you, and that he may establish the word which the LORD swore\nto your fathers, to Ibrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 9:6"}, "Know therefore that Allah your LORD doesn\u2019t give you this good land to possess for your righteousness, for you are a\nstiff-necked people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 9:7"}, "Remember, and don\u2019t forget, how you provoked Allah your LORD to wrath in the wilderness. From the day that you left the\nland of Egypt until you came to this place, you have been rebellious against the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 9:8"}, "Also in Horeb you provoked the LORD to wrath, and the LORD was angry with you to destroy you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 9:9"}, "When I had gone up onto the mountain to receive the stone tablets, even the tablets of the covenant which the LORD made\nwith you, then I stayed on the mountain forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread nor drank water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 9:10"}, "The LORD delivered to me the two stone tablets written with Allah\u2019s finger. On them were all the words which the LORD\nspoke with you on the mountain out of the middle of the fire in the day of the assembly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 9:11"}, "It came to pass at the end of forty days and forty nights that the LORD gave me the two stone tablets, even the tablets\nof the covenant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 9:12"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cArise, get down quickly from here; for your people whom you have brought out of Egypt have\ncorrupted themselves. They have quickly turned away from the way which I commanded them. They have made a molten image for\nthemselves!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 9:13"}, "Furthermore the LORD spoke to me, saying, \u201cI have seen this people, and behold, it is a stiff-necked people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 9:14"}, "Leave me alone, that I may destroy them, and blot out their name from under the sky; and I will make of you a nation\nmightier and greater than they.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 9:15"}, "So I turned and came down from the mountain, and the mountain was burning with fire. The two tablets of the covenant were\nin my two hands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 9:16"}, "I looked, and behold, you had sinned against Allah your LORD. You had made yourselves a moulded calf. You had quickly\nturned away from the way which the LORD had commanded you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 9:17"}, "I took hold of the two tablets, and threw them out of my two hands, and broke them before your eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 9:18"}, "I fell down before the LORD, as at the first, forty days and forty nights. I neither ate bread nor drank water, because\nof all your sin which you sinned, in doing that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, to provoke him to anger.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 9:19"}, "For I was afraid of the anger and hot displeasure with which the LORD was angry against you to destroy you. But the LORD\nlistened to me that time also. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 9:20"}, "The LORD was angry enough with Harun to destroy him. I prayed for Harun also at the same time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 9:21"}, "I took your sin, the calf which you had made, and burnt it with fire, and crushed it, grinding it very small, until it\nwas as fine as dust. I threw its dust into the brook that descended out of the mountain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 9:22"}, "At Taberah, at Massah, and at Kibroth Hattaavah you provoked the LORD to wrath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 9:23"}, "When the LORD sent you from Kadesh Barnea, saying, \u201cGo up and possess the land which I have given you,\u201d you rebelled\nagainst the commandment of Allah your LORD, and you didn\u2019t believe him or listen to his voice.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 9:24"}, "You have been rebellious against the LORD from the day that I knew you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 9:25"}, "So I fell down before the LORD the forty days and forty nights that I fell down, because the LORD had said he would\ndestroy you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 9:26"}, "I prayed to the LORD, and said, \u201cLord ALLAH, don\u2019t destroy your people and your inheritance that you have redeemed\nthrough your greatness, that you have brought out of Egypt with a mighty hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 9:27"}, "Remember your servants, Ibrahim, Is\u1e25\u0101q, and Yaqub. Don\u2019t look at the stubbornness of this people, nor at their\nwickedness, nor at their sin, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 9:28"}, "lest the land you brought us out from say, \u2018Because the LORD was not able to bring them into the land which he promised\nto them, and because he hated them, he has brought them out to kill them in the wilderness.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 9:29"}, "Yet they are your people and your inheritance, which you brought out by your great power and by your outstretched arm.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 10:1"}, "At that time the LORD said to me, \u201cCut two stone tablets like the first, and come up to me onto the mountain, and make an\nark of wood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 10:2"}, "I will write on the tablets the words that were on the first tablets which you broke, and you shall put them in the ark.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 10:3"}, "So I made an ark of acacia wood, and cut two stone tablets like the first, and went up onto the mountain, having the two\ntablets in my hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 10:4"}, "He wrote on the tablets, according to the first writing, the ten commandments, which the LORD spoke to you on the mountain\nout of the middle of the fire in the day of the assembly; and the LORD gave them to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 10:5"}, "I turned and came down from the mountain, and put the tablets in the ark which I had made; and there they are as the LORD\ncommanded me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 10:6"}, "(The children of Israel travelled from Beeroth Bene Jaakan to Moserah. There Harun died, and there he was buried; and\nEleazar his son ministered in the priest\u2019s office in his place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 10:7"}, "From there they travelled to Gudgodah; and from Gudgodah to Jotbathah, a land of brooks of water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 10:8"}, "At that time the LORD set apart the tribe of Levi to bear the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant, to stand before the LORD to\nminister to him, and to bless in his name, to this day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 10:9"}, "Therefore Levi has no portion nor inheritance with his brothers; the LORD is his inheritance, according as Allah your LORD\nspoke to him.) \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 10:10"}, "I stayed on the mountain, as at the first time, forty days and forty nights; and the LORD listened to me that time also.\nThe LORD would not destroy you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 10:11"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cArise, take your journey before the people; and they shall go in and possess the land which I swore\nto their fathers to give to them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 10:12"}, "Now, Israel, what does Allah your LORD require of you, but to fear Allah your LORD, to walk in all his ways, to love him,\nand to serve Allah your LORD with all your heart and with all your soul,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 10:13"}, "to keep the LORD\u2019s commandments and statutes, which I command you today for your good?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 10:14"}, "Behold, to Allah your LORD belongs heaven, the heaven of heavens, and the earth, with all that is therein.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 10:15"}, "Only the LORD had a delight in your fathers to love them, and he chose their offspring after them, even you above all\npeoples, as it is today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 10:16"}, "Circumcise therefore the foreskin of your heart, and be no more stiff-necked.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 10:17"}, "For Allah your LORD, he is Allah of gods and Lord of lords, the great Allah, the mighty, and the awesome, who doesn\u2019t\nrespect persons or take bribes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 10:18"}, "He executes justice for the fatherless and widow and loves the foreigner in giving him food and clothing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 10:19"}, "Therefore love the foreigner, for you were foreigners in the land of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 10:20"}, "You shall fear Allah your LORD. You shall serve him. You shall cling to him, and you shall swear by his name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 10:21"}, "He is your praise, and he is your Allah, who has done for you these great and awesome things which your eyes have seen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 10:22"}, "Your fathers went down into Egypt with seventy persons; and now Allah your LORD has made you as the stars of the sky for\nmultitude. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 11:1"}, "Therefore you shall love Allah your LORD, and keep his instructions, his statutes, his ordinances, and his commandments,\nalways. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 11:2"}, "Know this day\u2014for I don\u2019t speak with your children who have not known, and who have not seen the chastisement of Allah\nyour LORD, his greatness, his mighty hand, his outstretched arm,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 11:3"}, "his signs, and his works, which he did in the middle of Egypt to Pharaoh the king of Egypt, and to all his land;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 11:4"}, "and what he did to the army of Egypt, to their horses, and to their chariots; how he made the water of the Red Sea to\noverflow them as they pursued you, and how the LORD has destroyed them to this day;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 11:5"}, "and what he did to you in the wilderness until you came to this place;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 11:6"}, "and what he did to Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, the son of Reuben\u2014how the earth opened its mouth and swallowed\nthem up, with their households, their tents, and every living thing that followed them, in the middle of all Israel;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 11:7"}, "but your eyes have seen all of the LORD\u2019s great work which he did.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 11:8"}, "Therefore you shall keep the entire commandment which I command you today, that you may be strong, and go in and possess\nthe land that you go over to possess; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 11:9"}, "and that you may prolong your days in the land which the LORD swore to your fathers to give to them and to their\noffspring, a land flowing with milk and honey. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 11:10"}, "For the land, where you go in to possess isn\u2019t like the land of Egypt that you came out of, where you sowed your seed and\nwatered it with your foot, as a garden of herbs; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 11:11"}, "but the land that you go over to possess is a land of hills and valleys which drinks water from the rain of the sky,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 11:12"}, "a land which Allah your LORD cares for. The LORD your Allah\u2019s eyes are always on it, from the beginning of the year even\nto the end of the year. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 11:13"}, "It shall happen, if you shall listen diligently to my commandments which I command you today, to love Allah your LORD,\nand to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 11:14"}, "that I will give the rain for your land in its season, the early rain and the latter rain, that you may gather in your\ngrain, your new wine, and your oil. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 11:15"}, "I will give grass in your fields for your livestock, and you shall eat and be full.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 11:16"}, "Be careful, lest your heart be deceived, and you turn away to serve other gods and worship them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 11:17"}, "and the LORD\u2019s anger be kindled against you, and he shut up the sky so that there is no rain, and the land doesn\u2019t yield\nits fruit; and you perish quickly from off the good land which the LORD gives you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 11:18"}, "Therefore you shall lay up these words of mine in your heart and in your soul. You shall bind them for a sign on your\nhand, and they shall be for frontlets between your eyes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 11:19"}, "You shall teach them to your children, talking of them when you sit in your house, when you walk by the way, when you lie\ndown, and when you rise up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 11:20"}, "You shall write them on the door posts of your house and on your gates;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 11:21"}, "that your days and your children\u2019s days may be multiplied in the land which the LORD swore to your fathers to give them,\nas the days of the heavens above the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 11:22"}, "For if you shall diligently keep all these commandments which I command you\u2014to do them, to love Allah your LORD, to walk\nin all his ways, and to cling to him\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 11:23"}, "then the LORD will drive out all these nations from before you, and you shall dispossess nations greater and mightier\nthan yourselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 11:24"}, "Every place on which the sole of your foot treads shall be yours: from the wilderness and Lebanon, from the river, the\nriver Euphrates, even to the western sea shall be your border. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 11:25"}, "No man will be able to stand before you. The LORD your Allah will lay the fear of you and the dread of you on all the\nland that you tread on, as he has spoken to you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 11:26"}, "Behold, I set before you today a blessing and a curse: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 11:27"}, "the blessing, if you listen to the commandments of Allah your LORD, which I command you today;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 11:28"}, "and the curse, if you do not listen to the commandments of Allah your LORD, but turn away out of the way which I command\nyou today, to go after other gods which you have not known. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 11:29"}, "It shall happen, when Allah your LORD brings you into the land that you go to possess, that you shall set the blessing on\nMount Gerizim, and the curse on Mount Ebal. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 11:30"}, "Aren\u2019t they beyond the Jordan, behind the way of the going down of the sun, in the land of the Canaanites who dwell in\nthe Arabah near Gilgal, beside the oaks of Moreh? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 11:31"}, "For you are to pass over the Jordan to go in to possess the land which Allah your LORD gives you, and you shall possess\nit and dwell in it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 11:32"}, "You shall observe to do all the statutes and the ordinances which I set before you today.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 12:1"}, "These are the statutes and the ordinances which you shall observe to do in the land which the LORD, Allah of your fathers,\nhas given you to possess all the days that you live on the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 12:2"}, "You shall surely destroy all the places in which the nations that you shall dispossess served their gods: on the high\nmountains, and on the hills, and under every green tree. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 12:3"}, "You shall break down their altars, dash their pillars in pieces, and burn their Asherah poles with fire. You shall cut\ndown the engraved images of their gods. You shall destroy their name out of that place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 12:4"}, "You shall not do so to Allah your LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 12:5"}, "But to the place which Allah your LORD shall choose out of all your tribes, to put his name there, you shall seek his\nhabitation, and you shall come there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 12:6"}, "You shall bring your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your tithes, the wave offering of your hand, your vows, your free\nwill offerings, and the firstborn of your herd and of your flock there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 12:7"}, "There you shall eat before Allah your LORD, and you shall rejoice in all that you put your hand to, you and your\nhouseholds, in which Allah your LORD has blessed you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 12:8"}, "You shall not do all the things that we do here today, every man whatever is right in his own eyes;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 12:9"}, "for you haven\u2019t yet come to the rest and to the inheritance which Allah your LORD gives you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 12:10"}, "But when you go over the Jordan and dwell in the land which Allah your LORD causes you to inherit, and he gives you rest\nfrom all your enemies around you, so that you dwell in safety, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 12:11"}, "then it shall happen that to the place which Allah your LORD shall choose, to cause his name to dwell there, there you\nshall bring all that I command you: your burnt offerings, your sacrifices, your tithes, the wave offering of your hand, and all\nyour choice vows which you vow to the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 12:12"}, "You shall rejoice before Allah your LORD\u2014you, and your sons, your daughters, your male servants, your female servants,\nand the Levite who is within your gates, because he has no portion nor inheritance with you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 12:13"}, "Be careful that you don\u2019t offer your burnt offerings in every place that you see;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 12:14"}, "but in the place which the LORD chooses in one of your tribes, there you shall offer your burnt offerings, and there you\nshall do all that I command you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 12:15"}, "Yet you may kill and eat meat within all your gates, after all the desire of your soul, according to Allah your LORD\u2019s\nblessing which he has given you. The unclean and the clean may eat of it, as of the gazelle and the deer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 12:16"}, "Only you shall not eat the blood. You shall pour it out on the earth like water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 12:17"}, "You may not eat within your gates the tithe of your grain, or of your new wine, or of your oil, or the firstborn of your\nherd or of your flock, nor any of your vows which you vow, nor your free will offerings, nor the wave offering of your hand;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 12:18"}, "but you shall eat them before Allah your LORD in the place which Allah your LORD shall choose: you, your son, your\ndaughter, your male servant, your female servant, and the Levite who is within your gates. You shall rejoice before Allah your\nLORD in all that you put your hand to. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 12:19"}, "Be careful that you don\u2019t forsake the Levite as long as you live in your land.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 12:20"}, "When Allah your LORD enlarges your border, as he has promised you, and you say, \u201cI want to eat meat,\u201d because your soul\ndesires to eat meat, you may eat meat, after all the desire of your soul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 12:21"}, "If the place which Allah your LORD shall choose to put his name is too far from you, then you shall kill of your herd and\nof your flock, which the LORD has given you, as I have commanded you; and you may eat within your gates, after all the desire\nof your soul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 12:22"}, "Even as the gazelle and as the deer is eaten, so you shall eat of it. The unclean and the clean may eat of it alike.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 12:23"}, "Only be sure that you don\u2019t eat the blood; for the blood is the life. You shall not eat the life with the meat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 12:24"}, "You shall not eat it. You shall pour it out on the earth like water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 12:25"}, "You shall not eat it, that it may go well with you and with your children after you, when you do that which is right in\nthe LORD\u2019s eyes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 12:26"}, "Only your holy things which you have, and your vows, you shall take and go to the place which the LORD shall choose.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 12:27"}, "You shall offer your burnt offerings, the meat and the blood, on Allah your LORD\u2019s altar. The blood of your sacrifices\nshall be poured out on Allah your LORD\u2019s altar, and you shall eat the meat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 12:28"}, "Observe and hear all these words which I command you, that it may go well with you and with your children after you\nforever, when you do that which is good and right in Allah your LORD\u2019s eyes.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 12:29"}, "When Allah your LORD cuts off the nations from before you where you go in to dispossess them, and you dispossess them and\ndwell in their land, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 12:30"}, "be careful that you are not ensnared to follow them after they are destroyed from before you, and that you not enquire\nafter their gods, saying, \u201cHow do these nations serve their gods? I will do likewise.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 12:31"}, "You shall not do so to Allah your LORD; for every abomination to the LORD, which he hates, they have done to their gods;\nfor they even burn their sons and their daughters in the fire to their gods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 12:32"}, "Whatever thing I command you, that you shall observe to do. You shall not add to it, nor take away from it.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 13:1"}, "If a prophet or a dreamer of dreams arises amongst you, and he gives you a sign or a wonder,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 13:2"}, "and the sign or the wonder comes to pass, of which he spoke to you, saying, \u201cLet\u2019s go after other gods\u201d (which you have\nnot known) \u201cand let\u2019s serve them,\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 13:3"}, "you shall not listen to the words of that prophet, or to that dreamer of dreams; for Allah your LORD is testing you, to\nknow whether you love Allah your LORD with all your heart and with all your soul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 13:4"}, "You shall walk after Allah your LORD, fear him, keep his commandments, and obey his voice. You shall serve him, and cling\nto him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 13:5"}, "That prophet, or that dreamer of dreams, shall be put to death, because he has spoken rebellion against Allah your LORD,\nwho brought you out of the land of Egypt and redeemed you out of the house of bondage, to draw you aside out of the way which\nAllah your LORD commanded you to walk in. So you shall remove the evil from amongst you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 13:6"}, "If your brother, the son of your mother, or your son, or your daughter, or the wife of your bosom, or your friend who is\nas your own soul, entices you secretly, saying, \u201cLet\u2019s go and serve other gods\u201d\u2014which you have not known, you, nor your\nfathers; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 13:7"}, "of the gods of the peoples who are around you, near to you, or far off from you, from the one end of the earth even to the\nother end of the earth\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 13:8"}, "you shall not consent to him nor listen to him; neither shall your eye pity him, neither shall you spare, neither shall\nyou conceal him; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 13:9"}, "but you shall surely kill him. Your hand shall be first on him to put him to death, and afterwards the hands of all the\npeople. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 13:10"}, "You shall stone him to death with stones, because he has sought to draw you away from Allah your LORD, who brought you\nout of the land of Egypt, out of the house of bondage. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 13:11"}, "All Israel shall hear, and fear, and shall not do any more wickedness like this amongst you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 13:12"}, "If you hear about one of your cities, which Allah your LORD gives you to dwell there, that\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 13:13"}, "certain wicked fellows have gone out from amongst you and have drawn away the inhabitants of their city, saying, \u201cLet\u2019s\ngo and serve other gods,\u201d which you have not known, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 13:14"}, "then you shall enquire, investigate, and ask diligently. Behold, if it is true, and the thing certain, that such\nabomination was done amongst you, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 13:15"}, "you shall surely strike the inhabitants of that city with the edge of the sword, destroying it utterly, with all that is\ntherein and its livestock, with the edge of the sword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 13:16"}, "You shall gather all its plunder into the middle of its street, and shall burn with fire the city, with all of its\nplunder, to Allah your LORD. It shall be a heap forever. It shall not be built again.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 13:17"}, "Nothing of the devoted thing shall cling to your hand, that the LORD may turn from the fierceness of his anger and show\nyou mercy, and have compassion on you and multiply you, as he has sworn to your fathers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 13:18"}, "when you listen to Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, to keep all his commandments which I command you today, to do that which is\nright in Allah your LORD\u2019s eyes. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 14:1"}, "You are the children of Allah your LORD. You shall not cut yourselves, nor make any baldness between your eyes for the\ndead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 14:2"}, "For you are a holy people to Allah your LORD, and the LORD has chosen you to be a people for his own possession, above all\npeoples who are on the face of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 14:3"}, "You shall not eat any abominable thing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 14:4"}, "These are the animals which you may eat: the ox, the sheep, the goat,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 14:5"}, "the deer, the gazelle, the roebuck, the wild goat, the ibex, the antelope, and the chamois.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 14:6"}, "Every animal that parts the hoof, and has the hoof split in two and chews the cud, amongst the animals, you may eat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 14:7"}, "Nevertheless these you shall not eat of them that chew the cud, or of those who have the hoof split: the camel, the hare,\nand the rabbit. Because they chew the cud but don\u2019t part the hoof, they are unclean to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 14:8"}, "The pig, because it has a split hoof but doesn\u2019t chew the cud, is unclean to you. You shall not eat their meat. You shall\nnot touch their carcasses. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 14:9"}, "These you may eat of all that are in the waters: you may eat whatever has fins and scales.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 14:10"}, "You shall not eat whatever doesn\u2019t have fins and scales. It is unclean to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 14:11"}, "Of all clean birds you may eat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 14:12"}, "But these are they of which you shall not eat: the eagle, the vulture, the osprey,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 14:13"}, "the red kite, the falcon, the kite after its kind, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 14:14"}, "every raven after its kind, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 14:15"}, "the ostrich, the owl, the seagull, the hawk after its kind,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 14:16"}, "the little owl, the great owl, the horned owl, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 14:17"}, "the pelican, the vulture, the cormorant, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 14:18"}, "the stork, the heron after its kind, the hoopoe, and the bat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 14:19"}, "All winged creeping things are unclean to you. They shall not be eaten.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 14:20"}, "Of all clean birds you may eat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 14:21"}, "You shall not eat of anything that dies of itself. You may give it to the foreigner living amongst you who is within your\ngates, that he may eat it; or you may sell it to a foreigner; for you are a holy people to Allah your LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["You shall not boil a young goat in its mother\u2019s milk. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 14:22"}, "You shall surely tithe all the increase of your seed, that which comes out of the field year by year.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 14:23"}, "You shall eat before Allah your LORD, in the place which he chooses to cause his name to dwell, the tithe of your grain,\nof your new wine, and of your oil, and the firstborn of your herd and of your flock; that you may learn to fear Allah your LORD\nalways. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 14:24"}, "If the way is too long for you, so that you are not able to carry it because the place which Allah your LORD shall choose\nto set his name there is too far from you, when Allah your LORD blesses you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 14:25"}, "then you shall turn it into money, bind up the money in your hand, and shall go to the place which Allah your LORD shall\nchoose. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 14:26"}, "You shall trade the money for whatever your soul desires: for cattle, or for sheep, or for wine, or for strong drink, or\nfor whatever your soul asks of you. You shall eat there before Allah your LORD, and you shall rejoice, you and your household.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 14:27"}, "You shall not forsake the Levite who is within your gates, for he has no portion nor inheritance with you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 14:28"}, "At the end of every three years you shall bring all the tithe of your increase in the same year, and shall store it\nwithin your gates. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 14:29"}, "The Levite, because he has no portion nor inheritance with you, as well as the foreigner living amongst you, the\nfatherless, and the widow who are within your gates shall come, and shall eat and be satisfied; that Allah your LORD may bless\nyou in all the work of your hand which you do. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 15:1"}, "At the end of every seven years, you shall cancel debts. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 15:2"}, "This is the way it shall be done: every creditor shall release that which he has lent to his neighbour. He shall not\nrequire payment from his neighbour and his brother, because the LORD\u2019s release has been proclaimed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 15:3"}, "Of a foreigner you may require it; but whatever of yours is with your brother, your hand shall release.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 15:4"}, "However there will be no poor with you (for the LORD will surely bless you in the land which Allah your LORD gives you for\nan inheritance to possess) \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 15:5"}, "if only you diligently listen to Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, to observe to do all this commandment which I command you today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 15:6"}, "For Allah your LORD will bless you, as he promised you. You will lend to many nations, but you will not borrow. You will\nrule over many nations, but they will not rule over you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 15:7"}, "If a poor man, one of your brothers, is with you within any of your gates in your land which Allah your LORD gives you,\nyou shall not harden your heart, nor shut your hand from your poor brother;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 15:8"}, "but you shall surely open your hand to him, and shall surely lend him sufficient for his need, which he lacks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 15:9"}, "Beware that there not be a wicked thought in your heart, saying, \u201cThe seventh year, the year of release, is at hand,\u201d and\nyour eye be evil against your poor brother and you give him nothing; and he cry to the LORD against you, and it be sin to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 15:10"}, "You shall surely give, and your heart shall not be grieved when you give to him, because it is for this thing Allah your\nLORD will bless you in all your work and in all that you put your hand to.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 15:11"}, "For the poor will never cease out of the land. Therefore I command you to surely open your hand to your brother, to your\nneedy, and to your poor, in your land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 15:12"}, "If your brother, a Hebrew man, or a Hebrew woman, is sold to you and serves you six years, then in the seventh year you\nshall let him go free from you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 15:13"}, "When you let him go free from you, you shall not let him go empty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 15:14"}, "You shall furnish him liberally out of your flock, out of your threshing floor, and out of your wine press. As Allah your\nLORD has blessed you, you shall give to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 15:15"}, "You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt, and Allah your LORD redeemed you. Therefore I command you\nthis thing today. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 15:16"}, "It shall be, if he tells you, \u201cI will not go out from you,\u201d because he loves you and your house, because he is well with\nyou, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 15:17"}, "then you shall take an awl, and thrust it through his ear to the door, and he shall be your servant forever. Also to your\nfemale servant you shall do likewise. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 15:18"}, "It shall not seem hard to you when you let him go free from you; for he has been double the value of a hired hand as he\nserved you six years. The LORD your Allah will bless you in all that you do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 15:19"}, "You shall dedicate all the firstborn males that are born of your herd and of your flock to Allah your LORD. You shall do\nno work with the firstborn of your herd, nor shear the firstborn of your flock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 15:20"}, "You shall eat it before Allah your LORD year by year in the place which the LORD shall choose, you and your household.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 15:21"}, "If it has any defect\u2014is lame or blind, or has any defect whatever, you shall not sacrifice it to Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 15:22"}, "You shall eat it within your gates. The unclean and the clean shall eat it alike, as the gazelle and as the deer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 15:23"}, "Only you shall not eat its blood. You shall pour it out on the ground like water.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 16:1"}, "Observe the month of Abib, and keep the Passover to Allah your LORD; for in the month of Abib Allah your LORD brought you\nout of Egypt by night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 16:2"}, "You shall sacrifice the Passover to Allah your LORD, of the flock and the herd, in the place which the LORD shall choose\nto cause his name to dwell there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 16:3"}, "You shall eat no leavened bread with it. You shall eat unleavened bread with it seven days, even the bread of affliction\n(for you came out of the land of Egypt in haste) that you may remember the day when you came out of the land of Egypt all the\ndays of your life. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 16:4"}, "No yeast shall be seen with you in all your borders seven days; neither shall any of the meat, which you sacrifice the\nfirst day at evening, remain all night until the morning. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 16:5"}, "You may not sacrifice the Passover within any of your gates which Allah your LORD gives you;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 16:6"}, "but at the place which Allah your LORD shall choose to cause his name to dwell in, there you shall sacrifice the Passover\nat evening, at the going down of the sun, at the season that you came out of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 16:7"}, "You shall roast and eat it in the place which Allah your LORD chooses. In the morning you shall return to your tents.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 16:8"}, "Six days you shall eat unleavened bread. On the seventh day shall be a solemn assembly to Allah your LORD. You shall do no\nwork. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 16:9"}, "You shall count for yourselves seven weeks. From the time you begin to put the sickle to the standing grain you shall\nbegin to count seven weeks. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 16:10"}, "You shall keep the feast of weeks to Allah your LORD with a tribute of a free will offering of your hand, which you shall\ngive according to how Allah your LORD blesses you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 16:11"}, "You shall rejoice before Allah your LORD: you, your son, your daughter, your male servant, your female servant, the\nLevite who is within your gates, the foreigner, the fatherless, and the widow who are amongst you, in the place which Allah\nyour LORD shall choose to cause his name to dwell there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 16:12"}, "You shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt. You shall observe and do these statutes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 16:13"}, "You shall keep the feast of booths seven days, after you have gathered in from your threshing floor and from your wine\npress. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 16:14"}, "You shall rejoice in your feast, you, your son, your daughter, your male servant, your female servant, the Levite, the\nforeigner, the fatherless, and the widow who are within your gates.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 16:15"}, "You shall keep a feast to Allah your LORD seven days in the place which the LORD chooses, because Allah your LORD will\nbless you in all your increase and in all the work of your hands, and you shall be altogether joyful.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 16:16"}, "Three times in a year all of your males shall appear before Allah your LORD in the place which he chooses: in the feast\nof unleavened bread, in the feast of weeks, and in the feast of booths. They shall not appear before the LORD empty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 16:17"}, "Every man shall give as he is able, according to Allah your LORD\u2019s blessing which he has given you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 16:18"}, "You shall make judges and officers in all your gates, which Allah your LORD gives you, according to your tribes; and they\nshall judge the people with righteous judgement. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 16:19"}, "You shall not pervert justice. You shall not show partiality. You shall not take a bribe, for a bribe blinds the eyes of\nthe wise and perverts the words of the righteous. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 16:20"}, "You shall follow that which is altogether just, that you may live and inherit the land which Allah your LORD gives you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 16:21"}, "You shall not plant for yourselves an Asherah of any kind of tree beside Allah your LORD\u2019s altar, which you shall make\nfor yourselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 16:22"}, "Neither shall you set yourself up a sacred stone which Allah your LORD hates.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 17:1"}, "You shall not sacrifice to Allah your LORD an ox or a sheep in which is a defect or anything evil; for that is an\nabomination to Allah your LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 17:2"}, "If there is found amongst you, within any of your gates which Allah your LORD gives you, a man or woman who does that\nwhich is evil in Allah your LORD\u2019s sight in transgressing his covenant,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 17:3"}, "and has gone and served other gods and worshipped them, or the sun, or the moon, or any of the stars of the sky, which I\nhave not commanded, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 17:4"}, "and you are told, and you have heard of it, then you shall enquire diligently. Behold, if it is true, and the thing\ncertain, that such abomination is done in Israel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 17:5"}, "then you shall bring out that man or that woman who has done this evil thing to your gates, even that same man or woman;\nand you shall stone them to death with stones. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 17:6"}, "At the mouth of two witnesses, or three witnesses, he who is to die shall be put to death. At the mouth of one witness he\nshall not be put to death. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 17:7"}, "The hands of the witnesses shall be first on him to put him to death, and afterward the hands of all the people. So you\nshall remove the evil from amongst you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 17:8"}, "If there arises a matter too hard for you in judgement, between blood and blood, between plea and plea, and between stroke\nand stroke, being matters of controversy within your gates, then you shall arise, and go up to the place which Allah your LORD\nchooses. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 17:9"}, "You shall come to the priests who are Levites and to the judge who shall be in those days. You shall enquire, and they\nshall give you the verdict. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 17:10"}, "You shall do according to the decisions of the verdict which they shall give you from that place which the LORD chooses.\nYou shall observe to do according to all that they shall teach you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 17:11"}, "According to the decisions of the law which they shall teach you, and according to the judgement which they shall tell\nyou, you shall do. You shall not turn away from the sentence which they announce to you, to the right hand, nor to the left.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 17:12"}, "The man who does presumptuously in not listening to the priest who stands to minister there before Allah your LORD, or to\nthe judge, even that man shall die. You shall put away the evil from Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 17:13"}, "All the people shall hear and fear, and do no more presumptuously.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 17:14"}, "When you have come to the land which Allah your LORD gives you, and possess it and dwell in it, and say, \u201cI will set a\nking over me, like all the nations that are around me,\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 17:15"}, "you shall surely set him whom Allah your LORD chooses as king over yourselves. You shall set as king over you one from\namongst your brothers. You may not put a foreigner over you, who is not your brother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 17:16"}, "Only he shall not multiply horses to himself, nor cause the people to return to Egypt, to the end that he may multiply\nhorses; because the LORD has said to you, \u201cYou shall not go back that way again.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 17:17"}, "He shall not multiply wives to himself, that his heart not turn away. He shall not greatly multiply to himself silver and\ngold. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 17:18"}, "It shall be, when he sits on the throne of his kingdom, that he shall write himself a copy of this law in a book, out of\nthat which is before the Levitical priests. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 17:19"}, "It shall be with him, and he shall read from it all the days of his life, that he may learn to fear the LORD his Allah,\nto keep all the words of this law and these statutes, to do them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 17:20"}, "that his heart not be lifted up above his brothers, and that he not turn away from the commandment to the right hand, or\nto the left, to the end that he may prolong his days in his kingdom, he and his children, in the middle of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 18:1"}, "The priests and the Levites\u2014all the tribe of Levi\u2014shall have no portion nor inheritance with Israel. They shall eat the\nofferings of the LORD made by fire and his portion. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 18:2"}, "They shall have no inheritance amongst their brothers. The LORD is their inheritance, as he has spoken to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 18:3"}, "This shall be the priests\u2019 due from the people, from those who offer a sacrifice, whether it be ox or sheep, that they\nshall give to the priest: the shoulder, the two cheeks, and the inner parts.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 18:4"}, "You shall give him the first fruits of your grain, of your new wine, and of your oil, and the first of the fleece of your\nsheep. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 18:5"}, "For Allah your LORD has chosen him out of all your tribes to stand to minister in the LORD\u2019s name, him and his sons\nforever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 18:6"}, "If a Levite comes from any of your gates out of all Israel where he lives, and comes with all the desire of his soul to\nthe place which the LORD shall choose, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 18:7"}, "then he shall minister in the name of the LORD his Allah, as all his brothers the Levites do, who stand there before the\nLORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 18:8"}, "They shall have like portions to eat, in addition to that which comes from the sale of his family possessions.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 18:9"}, "When you have come into the land which Allah your LORD gives you, you shall not learn to imitate the abominations of those\nnations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 18:10"}, "There shall not be found with you anyone who makes his son or his daughter to pass through the fire, one who uses\ndivination, one who tells fortunes, or an enchanter, or a sorcerer,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 18:11"}, "or a charmer, or someone who consults with a familiar spirit, or a wizard, or a necromancer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 18:12"}, "For whoever does these things is an abomination to the LORD. Because of these abominations, Allah your LORD drives them\nout from before you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 18:13"}, "You shall be blameless with Allah your LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 18:14"}, "For these nations that you shall dispossess listen to those who practise sorcery and to diviners; but as for you, Allah\nyour LORD has not allowed you so to do. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 18:15"}, "The LORD your Allah will raise up to you a prophet from amongst you, of your brothers, like me. You shall listen to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 18:16"}, "This is according to all that you desired of Allah your LORD in Horeb in the day of the assembly, saying, \u201cLet me not\nhear again the LORD my Allah\u2019s voice, neither let me see this great fire any more, that I not die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 18:17"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cThey have well said that which they have spoken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 18:18"}, "I will raise them up a prophet from amongst their brothers, like you. I will put my words in his mouth, and he shall\nspeak to them all that I shall command him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 18:19"}, "It shall happen, that whoever will not listen to my words which he shall speak in my name, I will require it of him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 18:20"}, "But the prophet who speaks a word presumptuously in my name, which I have not commanded him to speak, or who speaks in\nthe name of other gods, that same prophet shall die.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 18:21"}, "You may say in your heart, \u201cHow shall we know the word which the LORD has not spoken?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 18:22"}, "When a prophet speaks in the LORD\u2019s name, if the thing doesn\u2019t follow, nor happen, that is the thing which the LORD has\nnot spoken. The prophet has spoken it presumptuously. You shall not be afraid of him.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 19:1"}, "When Allah your LORD cuts off the nations whose land Allah your LORD gives you, and you succeed them and dwell in their\ncities and in their houses, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 19:2"}, "you shall set apart three cities for yourselves in the middle of your land, which Allah your LORD gives you to possess.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 19:3"}, "You shall prepare the way, and divide the borders of your land which Allah your LORD causes you to inherit into three\nparts, that every man slayer may flee there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 19:4"}, "This is the case of the man slayer who shall flee there and live: Whoever kills his neighbour unintentionally, and didn\u2019t\nhate him in time past\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 19:5"}, "as when a man goes into the forest with his neighbour to chop wood and his hand swings the axe to cut down the tree, and\nthe head slips from the handle and hits his neighbour so that he dies\u2014he shall flee to one of these cities and live.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 19:6"}, "Otherwise, the avenger of blood might pursue the man slayer while hot anger is in his heart and overtake him, because the\nway is long, and strike him mortally, even though he was not worthy of death, because he didn\u2019t hate him in time past.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 19:7"}, "Therefore I command you to set apart three cities for yourselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 19:8"}, "If Allah your LORD enlarges your border, as he has sworn to your fathers, and gives you all the land which he promised to\ngive to your fathers; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 19:9"}, "and if you keep all this commandment to do it, which I command you today, to love Allah your LORD, and to walk ever in his\nways, then you shall add three cities more for yourselves, in addition to these three.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 19:10"}, "This is so that innocent blood will not be shed in the middle of your land which Allah your LORD gives you for an\ninheritance, leaving blood guilt on you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 19:11"}, "But if any man hates his neighbour, lies in wait for him, rises up against him, strikes him mortally so that he dies, and\nhe flees into one of these cities; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 19:12"}, "then the elders of his city shall send and bring him there, and deliver him into the hand of the avenger of blood, that\nhe may die. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 19:13"}, "Your eye shall not pity him, but you shall purge the innocent blood from Israel that it may go well with you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 19:14"}, "You shall not remove your neighbour\u2019s landmark, which they of old time have set, in your inheritance which you shall\ninherit, in the land that Allah your LORD gives you to possess. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 19:15"}, "One witness shall not rise up against a man for any iniquity, or for any sin that he sins. At the mouth of two witnesses,\nor at the mouth of three witnesses, shall a matter be established.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 19:16"}, "If an unrighteous witness rises up against any man to testify against him of wrongdoing,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 19:17"}, "then both the men, between whom the controversy is, shall stand before the LORD, before the priests and the judges who\nshall be in those days; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 19:18"}, "and the judges shall make diligent inquisition; and behold, if the witness is a false witness, and has testified falsely\nagainst his brother, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 19:19"}, "then you shall do to him as he had thought to do to his brother. So you shall remove the evil from amongst you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 19:20"}, "Those who remain shall hear, and fear, and will never again commit any such evil amongst you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 19:21"}, "Your eyes shall not pity: life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 20:1"}, "When you go out to battle against your enemies, and see horses, chariots, and a people more numerous than you, you shall\nnot be afraid of them; for Allah your LORD is with you, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 20:2"}, "It shall be, when you draw near to the battle, that the priest shall approach and speak to the people,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 20:3"}, "and shall tell them, \u201cHear, Israel, you draw near today to battle against your enemies. Don\u2019t let your heart faint! Don\u2019t\nbe afraid, nor tremble, neither be scared of them; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 20:4"}, "for Allah your LORD is he who goes with you, to fight for you against your enemies, to save you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 20:5"}, "The officers shall speak to the people, saying, \u201cWhat man is there who has built a new house, and has not dedicated it?\nLet him go and return to his house, lest he die in the battle, and another man dedicate it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 20:6"}, "What man is there who has planted a vineyard, and has not used its fruit? Let him go and return to his house, lest he die\nin the battle, and another man use its fruit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 20:7"}, "What man is there who has pledged to be married to a wife, and has not taken her? Let him go and return to his house, lest\nhe die in the battle, and another man take her.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 20:8"}, "The officers shall speak further to the people, and they shall say, \u201cWhat man is there who is fearful and faint-hearted?\nLet him go and return to his house, lest his brother\u2019s heart melt as his heart.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 20:9"}, "It shall be, when the officers have finished speaking to the people, that they shall appoint captains of armies at the\nhead of the people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 20:10"}, "When you draw near to a city to fight against it, then proclaim peace to it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 20:11"}, "It shall be, if it gives you answer of peace and opens to you, then it shall be that all the people who are found therein\nshall become forced labourers to you, and shall serve you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 20:12"}, "If it will make no peace with you, but will make war against you, then you shall besiege it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 20:13"}, "When Allah your LORD delivers it into your hand, you shall strike every male of it with the edge of the sword;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 20:14"}, "but the women, the little ones, the livestock, and all that is in the city, even all its plunder, you shall take for\nplunder for yourself. You may use the plunder of your enemies, which Allah your LORD has given you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 20:15"}, "Thus you shall do to all the cities which are very far off from you, which are not of the cities of these nations.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 20:16"}, "But of the cities of these peoples that Allah your LORD gives you for an inheritance, you shall save alive nothing that\nbreathes; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 20:17"}, "but you shall utterly destroy them: the Hittite, the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite,\nas Allah your LORD has commanded you; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 20:18"}, "that they not teach you to follow all their abominations, which they have done for their gods; so would you sin against\nAllah your LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 20:19"}, "When you shall besiege a city a long time, in making war against it to take it, you shall not destroy its trees by\nwielding an axe against them; for you may eat of them. You shall not cut them down, for is the tree of the field man, that it\nshould be besieged by you? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 20:20"}, "Only the trees that you know are not trees for food, you shall destroy and cut them down. You shall build bulwarks\nagainst the city that makes war with you, until it falls. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 21:1"}, "If someone is found slain in the land which Allah your LORD gives you to possess, lying in the field, and it isn\u2019t known\nwho has struck him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 21:2"}, "then your elders and your judges shall come out, and they shall measure to the cities which are around him who is slain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 21:3"}, "It shall be that the elders of the city which is nearest to the slain man shall take a heifer of the herd, which hasn\u2019t\nbeen worked with and which has not drawn in the yoke. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 21:4"}, "The elders of that city shall bring the heifer down to a valley with running water, which is neither ploughed nor sown,\nand shall break the heifer\u2019s neck there in the valley. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 21:5"}, "The priests the sons of Levi shall come near, for them Allah your LORD has chosen to minister to him, and to bless in the\nLORD\u2019s name; and according to their word shall every controversy and every assault be decided.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 21:6"}, "All the elders of that city which is nearest to the slain man shall wash their hands over the heifer whose neck was broken\nin the valley. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 21:7"}, "They shall answer and say, \u201cOur hands have not shed this blood, neither have our eyes seen it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 21:8"}, "Forgive, the LORD, your people Israel, whom you have redeemed, and don\u2019t allow innocent blood amongst your people Israel.\u201d\nThe blood shall be forgiven them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 21:9"}, "So you shall put away the innocent blood from amongst you, when you shall do that which is right in the LORD\u2019s eyes.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 21:10"}, "When you go out to battle against your enemies, and Allah your LORD delivers them into your hands and you carry them away\ncaptive, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 21:11"}, "and see amongst the captives a beautiful woman, and you are attracted to her, and desire to take her as your wife,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 21:12"}, "then you shall bring her home to your house. She shall shave her head and trim her nails.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 21:13"}, "She shall take off the clothing of her captivity, and shall remain in your house, and bewail her father and her mother a\nfull month. After that you shall go in to her and be her husband, and she shall be your wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 21:14"}, "It shall be, if you have no delight in her, then you shall let her go where she desires; but you shall not sell her at\nall for money. You shall not deal with her as a slave, because you have humbled her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 21:15"}, "If a man has two wives, the one beloved and the other hated, and they have borne him children, both the beloved and the\nhated, and if the firstborn son is hers who was hated, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 21:16"}, "then it shall be, in the day that he causes his sons to inherit that which he has, that he may not give the son of the\nbeloved the rights of the firstborn before the son of the hated, who is the firstborn;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 21:17"}, "but he shall acknowledge the firstborn, the son of the hated, by giving him a double portion of all that he has; for he\nis the beginning of his strength. The right of the firstborn is his.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 21:18"}, "If a man has a stubborn and rebellious son who will not obey the voice of his father or the voice of his mother, and\nthough they chasten him, will not listen to them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 21:19"}, "then his father and his mother shall take hold of him and bring him out to the elders of his city and to the gate of his\nplace. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 21:20"}, "They shall tell the elders of his city, \u201cThis our son is stubborn and rebellious. He will not obey our voice. He is a\nglutton and a drunkard.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 21:21"}, "All the men of his city shall stone him to death with stones. So you shall remove the evil from amongst you. All Israel\nshall hear, and fear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 21:22"}, "If a man has committed a sin worthy of death, and he is put to death, and you hang him on a tree,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 21:23"}, "his body shall not remain all night on the tree, but you shall surely bury him the same day; for he who is hanged is\naccursed of Allah. Don\u2019t defile your land which Allah your LORD gives you for an inheritance.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 22:1"}, "You shall not see your brother\u2019s ox or his sheep go astray and hide yourself from them. You shall surely bring them again\nto your brother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 22:2"}, "If your brother isn\u2019t near to you, or if you don\u2019t know him, then you shall bring it home to your house, and it shall be\nwith you until your brother comes looking for it, and you shall restore it to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 22:3"}, "So you shall do with his donkey. So you shall do with his garment. So you shall do with every lost thing of your\nbrother\u2019s, which he has lost and you have found. You may not hide yourself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 22:4"}, "You shall not see your brother\u2019s donkey or his ox fallen down by the way, and hide yourself from them. You shall surely\nhelp him to lift them up again. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 22:5"}, "A woman shall not wear men\u2019s clothing, neither shall a man put on women\u2019s clothing; for whoever does these things is an\nabomination to Allah your LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 22:6"}, "If you come across a bird\u2019s nest on the way, in any tree or on the ground, with young ones or eggs, and the hen sitting on\nthe young, or on the eggs, you shall not take the hen with the young.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 22:7"}, "You shall surely let the hen go, but the young you may take for yourself, that it may be well with you, and that you may\nprolong your days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 22:8"}, "When you build a new house, then you shall make a railing around your roof, so that you don\u2019t bring blood on your house if\nanyone falls from there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 22:9"}, "You shall not sow your vineyard with two kinds of seed, lest all the fruit be defiled, the seed which you have sown, and\nthe increase of the vineyard. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 22:10"}, "You shall not plough with an ox and a donkey together. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 22:11"}, "You shall not wear clothes of wool and linen woven together.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 22:12"}, "You shall make yourselves fringes", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, tassels"]}], "caller": "+"}, " on the four corners of your cloak with which you\ncover yourself. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 22:13"}, "If any man takes a wife, and goes in to her, hates her, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 22:14"}, "accuses her of shameful things, gives her a bad name, and says, \u201cI took this woman, and when I came near to her, I didn\u2019t\nfind in her the tokens of virginity;\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 22:15"}, "then the young lady\u2019s father and mother shall take and bring the tokens of the young lady\u2019s virginity to the elders of\nthe city in the gate. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 22:16"}, "The young lady\u2019s father shall tell the elders, \u201cI gave my daughter to this man as his wife, and he hates her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 22:17"}, "Behold, he has accused her of shameful things, saying, \u2018I didn\u2019t find in your daughter the tokens of virginity;\u2019 and yet\nthese are the tokens of my daughter\u2019s virginity.\u201d They shall spread the cloth before the elders of the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 22:18"}, "The elders of that city shall take the man and chastise him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 22:19"}, "They shall fine him one hundred shekels of silver,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:19\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 100 shekels is about a kilogram or 2.2\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and give them to the father of the young lady, because he has given a bad name to a virgin of Israel. She shall be\nhis wife. He may not put her away all his days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 22:20"}, "But if this thing is true, that the tokens of virginity were not found in the young lady,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 22:21"}, "then they shall bring out the young lady to the door of her father\u2019s house, and the men of her city shall stone her to\ndeath with stones, because she has done folly in Israel, to play the prostitute in her father\u2019s house. So you shall remove the\nevil from amongst you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 22:22"}, "If a man is found lying with a woman married to a husband, then they shall both die, the man who lay with the woman and\nthe woman. So you shall remove the evil from Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 22:23"}, "If there is a young lady who is a virgin pledged to be married to a husband, and a man finds her in the city, and lies\nwith her, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 22:24"}, "then you shall bring them both out to the gate of that city, and you shall stone them to death with stones; the lady,\nbecause she didn\u2019t cry, being in the city; and the man, because he has humbled his neighbour\u2019s wife. So you shall remove the\nevil from amongst you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 22:25"}, "But if the man finds the lady who is pledged to be married in the field, and the man forces her and lies with her, then\nonly the man who lay with her shall die; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 22:26"}, "but to the lady you shall do nothing. There is in the lady no sin worthy of death; for as when a man rises against his\nneighbour and kills him, even so is this matter; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 22:27"}, "for he found her in the field, the pledged to be married lady cried, and there was no one to save her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 22:28"}, "If a man finds a lady who is a virgin, who is not pledged to be married, grabs her and lies with her, and they are found,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 22:29"}, "then the man who lay with her shall give to the lady\u2019s father fifty\nshekels", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver. She shall be his wife, because he has humbled her. He may not put her away all his days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 22:30"}, "A man shall not take his father\u2019s wife, and shall not uncover his father\u2019s skirt.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 23:1"}, "He who is emasculated by crushing or cutting shall not enter into the LORD\u2019s assembly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 23:2"}, "A person born of a forbidden union shall not enter into the LORD\u2019s assembly; even to the tenth generation shall no one of\nhis enter into the LORD\u2019s assembly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 23:3"}, "An Ammonite or a Moabite shall not enter into the LORD\u2019s assembly; even to the tenth generation shall no one belonging to\nthem enter into the LORD\u2019s assembly forever, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 23:4"}, "because they didn\u2019t meet you with bread and with water on the way when you came out of Egypt, and because they hired\nagainst you Balaam the son of Beor from Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 23:5"}, "Nevertheless Allah your LORD wouldn\u2019t listen to Balaam, but Allah your LORD turned the curse into a blessing to you,\nbecause Allah your LORD loved you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 23:6"}, "You shall not seek their peace nor their prosperity all your days forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 23:7"}, "You shall not abhor an Edomite, for he is your brother. You shall not abhor an Egyptian, because you lived as a foreigner\nin his land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 23:8"}, "The children of the third generation who are born to them may enter into the LORD\u2019s assembly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 23:9"}, "When you go out and camp against your enemies, then you shall keep yourselves from every evil thing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 23:10"}, "If there is amongst you any man who is not clean by reason of that which happens to him by night, then shall he go\noutside of the camp. He shall not come within the camp; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 23:11"}, "but it shall be, when evening comes, he shall bathe himself in water. When the sun is down, he shall come within the\ncamp. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 23:12"}, "You shall have a place also outside of the camp where you go relieve yourself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 23:13"}, "You shall have a trowel amongst your weapons. It shall be, when you relieve yourself, you shall dig with it, and shall\nturn back and cover your excrement; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 23:14"}, "for Allah your LORD walks in the middle of your camp, to deliver you, and to give up your enemies before you. Therefore\nyour camp shall be holy, that he may not see an unclean thing in you, and turn away from you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 23:15"}, "You shall not deliver to his master a servant who has escaped from his master to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 23:16"}, "He shall dwell with you, amongst you, in the place which he shall choose within one of your gates, where it pleases him\nbest. You shall not oppress him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 23:17"}, "There shall be no prostitute of the daughters of Israel, neither shall there be a sodomite of the sons of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 23:18"}, "You shall not bring the hire of a prostitute, or the wages of a male\nprostitute,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, dog"]}], "caller": "+"}, " into the house of Allah your LORD for any vow; for both of these are an\nabomination to Allah your LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 23:19"}, "You shall not lend on interest to your brother: interest of money, interest of food, interest of anything that is lent on\ninterest. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 23:20"}, "You may charge a foreigner interest; but you shall not your brother interest, that Allah your LORD may bless you in all\nthat you put your hand to, in the land where you go in to possess it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 23:21"}, "When you vow a vow to Allah your LORD, you shall not be slack to pay it, for Allah your LORD will surely require it of\nyou; and it would be sin in you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 23:22"}, "But if you refrain from making a vow, it shall be no sin in you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 23:23"}, "You shall observe and do that which has gone out of your lips. Whatever you have vowed to Allah your LORD as a free will\noffering, which you have promised with your mouth, you must do. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 23:24"}, "When you come into your neighbour\u2019s vineyard, then you may eat your fill of grapes at your own pleasure; but you shall\nnot put any in your container. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 23:25"}, "When you come into your neighbour\u2019s standing grain, then you may pluck the ears with your hand; but you shall not use a\nsickle on your neighbour\u2019s standing grain. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 24:1"}, "When a man takes a wife and marries her, then it shall be, if she finds no favour in his eyes because he has found some\nunseemly thing in her, that he shall write her a certificate of divorce, put it in her hand, and send her out of his house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 24:2"}, "When she has departed out of his house, she may go and be another man\u2019s wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 24:3"}, "If the latter husband hates her, and write her a certificate of divorce, puts it in her hand, and sends her out of his\nhouse; or if the latter husband dies, who took her to be his wife;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 24:4"}, "her former husband, who sent her away, may not take her again to be his wife after she is defiled; for that would be an\nabomination to the LORD. You shall not cause the land to sin, which Allah your LORD gives you for an inheritance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 24:5"}, "When a man takes a new wife, he shall not go out in the army, neither shall he be assigned any business. He shall be free\nat home one year, and shall cheer his wife whom he has taken. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 24:6"}, "No man shall take the mill or the upper millstone as a pledge, for he takes a life in pledge.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 24:7"}, "If a man is found stealing any of his brothers of the children of Israel, and he deals with him as a slave, or sells him,\nthen that thief shall die. So you shall remove the evil from amongst you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 24:8"}, "Be careful in the plague of leprosy, that you observe diligently and do according to all that the Levitical priests teach\nyou. As I commanded them, so you shall observe to do. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 24:9"}, "Remember what Allah your LORD did to Miriam, by the way as you came out of Egypt.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 24:10"}, "When you lend your neighbour any kind of loan, you shall not go into his house to get his pledge.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 24:11"}, "You shall stand outside, and the man to whom you lend shall bring the pledge outside to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 24:12"}, "If he is a poor man, you shall not sleep with his pledge. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 24:13"}, "You shall surely restore to him the pledge when the sun goes down, that he may sleep in his garment and bless you. It\nshall be righteousness to you before Allah your LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 24:14"}, "You shall not oppress a hired servant who is poor and needy, whether he is one of your brothers or one of the foreigners\nwho are in your land within your gates. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 24:15"}, "In his day you shall give him his wages, neither shall the sun go down on it; for he is poor and sets his heart on it;\nlest he cry against you to the LORD, and it be sin to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 24:16"}, "The fathers shall not be put to death for the children, neither shall the children be put to death for the fathers. Every\nman shall be put to death for his own sin. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 24:17"}, "You shall not deprive the foreigner or the fatherless of justice, nor take a widow\u2019s clothing in pledge;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 24:18"}, "but you shall remember that you were a slave in Egypt, and Allah your LORD redeemed you there. Therefore I command you to\ndo this thing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 24:19"}, "When you reap your harvest in your field, and have forgotten a sheaf in the field, you shall not go again to get it. It\nshall be for the foreigner, for the fatherless, and for the widow, that Allah your LORD may bless you in all the work of your\nhands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 24:20"}, "When you beat your olive tree, you shall not go over the boughs again. It shall be for the foreigner, for the fatherless,\nand for the widow. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 24:21"}, "When you harvest your vineyard, you shall not glean it after yourselves. It shall be for the foreigner, for the\nfatherless, and for the widow. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 24:22"}, "You shall remember that you were a slave in the land of Egypt. Therefore I command you to do this thing.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 25:1"}, "If there is a controversy between men, and they come to judgement and the judges judge them, then they shall justify the\nrighteous and condemn the wicked. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 25:2"}, "It shall be, if the wicked man is worthy to be beaten, that the judge shall cause him to lie down and to be beaten before\nhis face, according to his wickedness, by number. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 25:3"}, "He may sentence him to no more than forty stripes. He shall not give more, lest if he should give more and beat him more\nthan that many stripes, then your brother will be degraded in your sight.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 25:4"}, "You shall not muzzle the ox when he treads out the grain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 25:5"}, "If brothers dwell together, and one of them dies and has no son, the wife of the dead shall not be married outside to a\nstranger. Her husband\u2019s brother shall go in to her, and take her as his wife, and perform the duty of a husband\u2019s brother to\nher. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 25:6"}, "It shall be that the firstborn whom she bears shall succeed in the name of his brother who is dead, that his name not be\nblotted out of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 25:7"}, "If the man doesn\u2019t want to take his brother\u2019s wife, then his brother\u2019s wife shall go up to the gate to the elders, and\nsay, \u201cMy husband\u2019s brother refuses to raise up to his brother a name in Israel. He will not perform the duty of a husband\u2019s\nbrother to me.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 25:8"}, "Then the elders of his city shall call him, and speak to him. If he stands and says, \u201cI don\u2019t want to take her,\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 25:9"}, "then his brother\u2019s wife shall come to him in the presence of the elders, and loose his sandal from off his foot, and spit\nin his face. She shall answer and say, \u201cSo shall it be done to the man who does not build up his brother\u2019s house.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 25:10"}, "His name shall be called in Israel, \u201cThe house of him who had his sandal removed.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 25:11"}, "When men strive against each other, and the wife of one draws near to deliver her husband out of the hand of him who\nstrikes him, and puts out her hand, and grabs him by his private parts,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 25:12"}, "then you shall cut off her hand. Your eye shall have no pity.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 25:13"}, "You shall not have in your bag diverse weights, one heavy and one light.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 25:14"}, "You shall not have in your house diverse measures, one large and one small.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 25:15"}, "You shall have a perfect and just weight. You shall have a perfect and just measure, that your days may be long in the\nland which Allah your LORD gives you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 25:16"}, "For all who do such things, all who do unrighteously, are an abomination to Allah your LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 25:17"}, "Remember what Amalek did to you by the way as you came out of Egypt;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 25:18"}, "how he met you by the way, and struck the rearmost of you, all who were feeble behind you, when you were faint and weary;\nand he didn\u2019t fear Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 25:19"}, "Therefore it shall be, when Allah your LORD has given you rest from all your enemies all around, in the land which Allah\nyour LORD gives you for an inheritance to possess it, that you shall blot out the memory of Amalek from under the sky. You\nshall not forget. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 26:1"}, "It shall be, when you have come in to the land which Allah your LORD gives you for an inheritance, possess it, and dwell\nin it, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 26:2"}, "that you shall take some of the first of all the fruit of the ground, which you shall bring in from your land that Allah\nyour LORD gives you. You shall put it in a basket, and shall go to the place which Allah your LORD shall choose to cause his\nname to dwell there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 26:3"}, "You shall come to the priest who shall be in those days, and tell him, \u201cI profess today to Allah your LORD, that I have\ncome to the land which the LORD swore to our fathers to give us.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 26:4"}, "The priest shall take the basket out of your hand, and set it down before Allah your LORD\u2019s altar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 26:5"}, "You shall answer and say before Allah your LORD, \u201cMy father", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["26:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, forefather"]}], "caller": "+"}, " was a Syrian ready to perish. He went down into Egypt, and lived there, few in number. There he\nbecame a great, mighty, and populous nation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 26:6"}, "The Egyptians mistreated us, afflicted us, and imposed hard labour on us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 26:7"}, "Then we cried to the LORD, Allah of our fathers. The LORD heard our voice, and saw our affliction, our toil, and our\noppression. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 26:8"}, "The LORD brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand, with an outstretched arm, with great terror, with signs, and with\nwonders; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 26:9"}, "and he has brought us into this place, and has given us this land, a land flowing with milk and honey.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 26:10"}, "Now, behold, I have brought the first of the fruit of the ground, which you, the LORD, have given me.\u201d You shall set it\ndown before Allah your LORD, and worship before Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 26:11"}, "You shall rejoice in all the good which Allah your LORD has given to you, and to your house, you, and the Levite, and the\nforeigner who is amongst you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 26:12"}, "When you have finished tithing all the tithe of your increase in the third year, which is the year of tithing, then you\nshall give it to the Levite, to the foreigner, to the fatherless, and to the widow, that they may eat within your gates and be\nfilled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 26:13"}, "You shall say before Allah your LORD, \u201cI have put away the holy things out of my house, and also have given them to the\nLevite, to the foreigner, to the fatherless, and to the widow, according to all your commandment which you have commanded me. I\nhave not transgressed any of your commandments, neither have I forgotten them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 26:14"}, "I have not eaten of it in my mourning, neither have I removed any of it while I was unclean, nor given of it for the\ndead. I have listened to the LORD my Allah\u2019s voice. I have done according to all that you have commanded me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 26:15"}, "Look down from your holy habitation, from heaven, and bless your people Israel, and the ground which you have given us,\nas you swore to our fathers, a land flowing with milk and honey.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 26:16"}, "Today Allah your LORD commands you to do these statutes and ordinances. You shall therefore keep and do them with all\nyour heart and with all your soul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 26:17"}, "You have declared today that the LORD is your Allah, and that you would walk in his ways, keep his statutes, his\ncommandments, and his ordinances, and listen to his voice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 26:18"}, "The LORD has declared today that you are a people for his own possession, as he has promised you, and that you should\nkeep all his commandments. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 26:19"}, "He will make you high above all nations that he has made, in praise, in name, and in honour; and that you may be a holy\npeople to Allah your LORD, as he has spoken. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 27:1"}, "Musa and the elders of Israel commanded the people, saying, \u201cKeep all the commandment which I command you today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 27:2"}, "It shall be on the day when you shall pass over the Jordan to the land which Allah your LORD gives you, that you shall set\nyourself up great stones, and coat them with plaster. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 27:3"}, "You shall write on them all the words of this law, when you have passed over, that you may go in to the land which Allah\nyour LORD gives you, a land flowing with milk and honey, as the LORD, Allah of your fathers, has promised you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 27:4"}, "It shall be, when you have crossed over the Jordan, that you shall set up these stones, which I command you today, on\nMount Ebal, and you shall coat them with plaster. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 27:5"}, "There you shall build an altar to Allah your LORD, an altar of stones. You shall not use any iron tool on them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 27:6"}, "You shall build Allah your LORD\u2019s altar of uncut stones. You shall offer burnt offerings on it to Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 27:7"}, "You shall sacrifice peace offerings, and shall eat there. You shall rejoice before Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 27:8"}, "You shall write on the stones all the words of this law very plainly.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 27:9"}, "Musa and the Levitical priests spoke to all Israel, saying, \u201cBe silent and listen, Israel! Today you have become the\npeople of Allah your LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 27:10"}, "You shall therefore obey Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, and do his commandments and his statutes, which I command you today.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 27:11"}, "Musa commanded the people the same day, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 27:12"}, "\u201cThese shall stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people, when you have crossed over the Jordan: Simeon, Levi, Judah,\nIssachar, Yusuf, and Benjamin. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 27:13"}, "These shall stand on Mount Ebal for the curse: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 27:14"}, "With a loud voice, the Levites shall say to all the men of Israel,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 27:15"}, "\u2018Cursed is the man who makes an engraved or molten image, an abomination to the LORD, the work of the hands of the\ncraftsman, and sets it up in secret.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall answer and say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 27:16"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who dishonours his father or his mother.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 27:17"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who removes his neighbour\u2019s landmark.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 27:18"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who leads the blind astray on the road.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 27:19"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who withholds justice from the foreigner, fatherless, and widow.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 27:20"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who lies with", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["27:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["i.e., has sexual relations\nwith"]}], "caller": "+"}, " his father\u2019s wife, because he dishonours his father\u2019s bed.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 27:21"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who lies with any kind of animal.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 27:22"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who lies with his sister, his father\u2019s daughter or his mother\u2019s daughter.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 27:23"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who lies with his mother-in-law.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 27:24"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who secretly kills his neighbour.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 27:25"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who takes a bribe to kill an innocent person.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 27:26"}, "\u2018Cursed is he who doesn\u2019t uphold the words of this law by doing them.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people shall say, \u2018Amen.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 28:1"}, "It shall happen, if you shall listen diligently to Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, to observe to do all his commandments which I\ncommand you today, that Allah your LORD will set you high above all the nations of the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 28:2"}, "All these blessings will come upon you, and overtake you, if you listen to Allah your LORD\u2019s voice.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 28:3"}, "You shall be blessed in the city, and you shall be blessed in the field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 28:4"}, "You shall be blessed in the fruit of your body, the fruit of your ground, the fruit of your animals, the increase of your\nlivestock, and the young of your flock. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 28:5"}, "Your basket and your kneading trough shall be blessed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 28:6"}, "You shall be blessed when you come in, and you shall be blessed when you go out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 28:7"}, "The LORD will cause your enemies who rise up against you to be struck before you. They will come out against you one way,\nand will flee before you seven ways. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 28:8"}, "The LORD will command the blessing on you in your barns, and in all that you put your hand to. He will bless you in the\nland which Allah your LORD gives you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 28:9"}, "The LORD will establish you for a holy people to himself, as he has sworn to you, if you shall keep the commandments of\nAllah your LORD, and walk in his ways. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 28:10"}, "All the peoples of the earth shall see that you are called by the LORD\u2019s name, and they will be afraid of you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 28:11"}, "The LORD will grant you abundant prosperity in the fruit of your body, in the fruit of your livestock, and in the fruit\nof your ground, in the land which the LORD swore to your fathers to give you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 28:12"}, "The LORD will open to you his good treasure in the sky, to give the rain of your land in its season, and to bless all the\nwork of your hand. You will lend to many nations, and you will not borrow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 28:13"}, "The LORD will make you the head, and not the tail. You will be above only, and you will not be beneath, if you listen to\nthe commandments of Allah your LORD which I command you today, to observe and to do,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 28:14"}, "and shall not turn away from any of the words which I command you today, to the right hand or to the left, to go after\nother gods to serve them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 28:15"}, "But it shall come to pass, if you will not listen to Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, to observe to do all his commandments and\nhis statutes which I command you today, that all these curses will come on you and overtake you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 28:16"}, "You will be cursed in the city, and you will be cursed in the field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 28:17"}, "Your basket and your kneading trough will be cursed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 28:18"}, "The fruit of your body, the fruit of your ground, the increase of your livestock, and the young of your flock will be\ncursed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 28:19"}, "You will be cursed when you come in, and you will be cursed when you go out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 28:20"}, "The LORD will send on you cursing, confusion, and rebuke in all that you put your hand to do, until you are destroyed and\nuntil you perish quickly, because of the evil of your doings, by which you have forsaken me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 28:21"}, "The LORD will make the pestilence cling to you, until he has consumed you from off the land where you go in to possess\nit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 28:22"}, "The LORD will strike you with consumption, with fever, with inflammation, with fiery heat, with the sword, with blight,\nand with mildew. They will pursue you until you perish. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 28:23"}, "Your sky that is over your head will be bronze, and the earth that is under you will be iron.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 28:24"}, "The LORD will make the rain of your land powder and dust. It will come down on you from the sky, until you are destroyed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 28:25"}, "The LORD will cause you to be struck before your enemies. You will go out one way against them, and will flee seven ways\nbefore them. You will be tossed back and forth amongst all the kingdoms of the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 28:26"}, "Your dead bodies will be food to all birds of the sky, and to the animals of the earth; and there will be no one to\nfrighten them away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 28:27"}, "The LORD will strike you with the boils of Egypt, with the tumours, with the scurvy, and with the itch, of which you can\nnot be healed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 28:28"}, "The LORD will strike you with madness, with blindness, and with astonishment of heart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 28:29"}, "You will grope at noonday, as the blind gropes in darkness, and you shall not prosper in your ways. You will only be\noppressed and robbed always, and there will be no one to save you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 28:30"}, "You will betroth a wife, and another man shall lie with her. You will build a house, and you won\u2019t dwell in it. You will\nplant a vineyard, and not use its fruit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 28:31"}, "Your ox will be slain before your eyes, and you will not eat any of it. Your donkey will be violently taken away from\nbefore your face, and will not be restored to you. Your sheep will be given to your enemies, and you will have no one to save\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 28:32"}, "Your sons and your daughters will be given to another people. Your eyes will look, and fail with longing for them all day\nlong. There will be no power in your hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 28:33"}, "A nation which you don\u2019t know will eat the fruit of your ground and all of your work. You will only be oppressed and\ncrushed always, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DEU 28:34"}, "so that the sights that you see with your eyes will drive you mad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DEU 28:35"}, "The LORD will strike you in the knees and in the legs with a sore boil, of which you cannot be healed, from the sole of\nyour foot to the crown of your head. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DEU 28:36"}, "The LORD will bring you, and your king whom you will set over yourselves, to a nation that you have not known, you nor\nyour fathers. There you will serve other gods of wood and stone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DEU 28:37"}, "You will become an astonishment, a proverb, and a byword amongst all the peoples where the LORD will lead you away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "DEU 28:38"}, "You will carry much seed out into the field, and will gather little in, for the locust will consume it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "DEU 28:39"}, "You will plant vineyards and dress them, but you will neither drink of the wine, nor harvest, because worms will eat\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "DEU 28:40"}, "You will have olive trees throughout all your borders, but you won\u2019t anoint yourself with the oil, for your olives will\ndrop off. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "DEU 28:41"}, "You will father sons and daughters, but they will not be yours, for they will go into captivity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "DEU 28:42"}, "Locusts will consume all of your trees and the fruit of your ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "DEU 28:43"}, "The foreigner who is amongst you will mount up above you higher and higher, and you will come down lower and lower.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "DEU 28:44"}, "He will lend to you, and you won\u2019t lend to him. He will be the head, and you will be the tail.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "DEU 28:45"}, "All these curses will come on you, and will pursue you and overtake you, until you are destroyed, because you didn\u2019t\nlisten to Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, to keep his commandments and his statutes which he commanded you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "DEU 28:46"}, "They will be for a sign and for a wonder to you and to your offspring forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "DEU 28:47"}, "Because you didn\u2019t serve Allah your LORD with joyfulness and with gladness of heart, by reason of the abundance of all\nthings; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "DEU 28:48"}, "therefore you will serve your enemies whom the LORD sends against you, in hunger, in thirst, in nakedness, and in lack of\nall things. He will put an iron yoke on your neck until he has destroyed you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "DEU 28:49"}, "The LORD will bring a nation against you from far, from the end of the earth, as the eagle flies: a nation whose language\nyou will not understand, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "DEU 28:50"}, "a nation of fierce facial expressions, that doesn\u2019t respect the elderly, nor show favour to the young.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "DEU 28:51"}, "They will eat the fruit of your livestock and the fruit of your ground, until you are destroyed. They also won\u2019t leave\nyou grain, new wine, oil, the increase of your livestock, or the young of your flock, until they have caused you to perish.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "DEU 28:52"}, "They will besiege you in all your gates until your high and fortified walls in which you trusted come down throughout all\nyour land. They will besiege you in all your gates throughout all your land which Allah your LORD has given you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "DEU 28:53"}, "You will eat the fruit of your own body, the flesh of your sons and of your daughters, whom Allah your LORD has given\nyou, in the siege and in the distress with which your enemies will distress you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "DEU 28:54"}, "The man who is tender amongst you, and very delicate, his eye will be evil towards his brother, towards the wife whom he\nloves, and towards the remnant of his children whom he has remaining,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "DEU 28:55"}, "so that he will not give to any of them of the flesh of his children whom he will eat, because he has nothing left to\nhim, in the siege and in the distress with which your enemy will distress you in all your gates.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "DEU 28:56"}, "The tender and delicate woman amongst you, who would not venture to set the sole of her foot on the ground for\ndelicateness and tenderness, her eye will be evil towards the husband that she loves, towards her son, towards her daughter,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "DEU 28:57"}, "towards her young one who comes out from between her feet, and towards her children whom she bears; for she will eat them\nsecretly for lack of all things in the siege and in the distress with which your enemy will distress you in your gates.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "DEU 28:58"}, "If you will not observe to do all the words of this law that are written in this book, that you may fear this glorious\nand fearful name, THE LORD your Allah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "DEU 28:59"}, "then the LORD will make your plagues and the plagues of your offspring fearful, even great plagues, and of long duration,\nand severe sicknesses, and of long duration. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "DEU 28:60"}, "He will bring on you again all the diseases of Egypt, which you were afraid of; and they will cling to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "DEU 28:61"}, "Also every sickness and every plague which is not written in the book of this law, the LORD will bring them on you until\nyou are destroyed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "DEU 28:62"}, "You will be left few in number, even though you were as the stars of the sky for multitude, because you didn\u2019t listen to\nAllah your LORD\u2019s voice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "DEU 28:63"}, "It will happen that as the LORD rejoiced over you to do you good, and to multiply you, so the LORD will rejoice over you\nto cause you to perish and to destroy you. You will be plucked from the land that you are going in to possess.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "DEU 28:64"}, "The LORD will scatter you amongst all peoples, from one end of the earth to the other end of the earth. There you will\nserve other gods which you have not known, you nor your fathers, even wood and stone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "DEU 28:65"}, "Amongst these nations you will find no ease, and there will be no rest for the sole of your foot; but the LORD will give\nyou there a trembling heart, failing of eyes, and pining of soul.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "DEU 28:66"}, "Your life will hang in doubt before you. You will be afraid night and day, and will have no assurance of your life.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "DEU 28:67"}, "In the morning you will say, \u201cI wish it were evening!\u201d and at evening you will say, \u201cI wish it were morning!\u201d for the\nfear of your heart which you will fear, and for the sights which your eyes will see.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "68", "sid": "DEU 28:68"}, "The LORD will bring you into Egypt again with ships, by the way of which I told to you that you would never see it again.\nThere you will offer yourselves to your enemies for male and female slaves, and nobody will buy you.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 29"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 29:1"}, "These are the words of the covenant which the LORD commanded Musa to make with the children of Israel in the land of Moab,\nin addition to the covenant which he made with them in Horeb. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 29:2"}, "Musa called to all Israel, and said to them: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Your eyes have seen all that the LORD did in the land of Egypt to Pharaoh, and to all his servants, and to all his land;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 29:3"}, "the great trials which your eyes saw, the signs, and those great wonders.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 29:4"}, "But the LORD has not given you a heart to know, eyes to see, and ears to hear, to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 29:5"}, "I have led you forty years in the wilderness. Your clothes have not grown old on you, and your sandals have not grown old\non your feet. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 29:6"}, "You have not eaten bread, neither have you drunk wine or strong drink, that you may know that I am Allah your LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 29:7"}, "When you came to this place, Sihon the king of Heshbon and Og the king of Bashan came out against us to battle, and we\nstruck them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 29:8"}, "We took their land, and gave it for an inheritance to the Reubenites, and to the Gadites, and to the half-tribe of the\nManassites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 29:9"}, "Therefore keep the words of this covenant and do them, that you may prosper in all that you do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 29:10"}, "All of you stand today in the presence of Allah your LORD: your heads, your tribes, your elders, and your officers, even\nall the men of Israel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 29:11"}, "your little ones, your wives, and the foreigners who are in the middle of your camps, from the one who cuts your wood to\nthe one who draws your water, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 29:12"}, "that you may enter into the covenant of Allah your LORD, and into his oath, which Allah your LORD makes with you today,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 29:13"}, "that he may establish you today as his people, and that he may be your Allah, as he spoke to you and as he swore to your\nfathers, to Ibrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 29:14"}, "Neither do I make this covenant and this oath with you only,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 29:15"}, "but with those who stand here with us today before the LORD our Allah, and also with those who are not here with us today\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 29:16"}, "(for you know how we lived in the land of Egypt, and how we came through the middle of the nations through which you\npassed; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 29:17"}, "and you have seen their abominations and their idols of wood, stone, silver, and gold, which were amongst them);\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 29:18"}, "lest there should be amongst you man, woman, family, or tribe whose heart turns away today from the LORD our Allah, to go\nto serve the gods of those nations; lest there should be amongst you a root that produces bitter poison;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 29:19"}, "and it happen, when he hears the words of this curse, that he bless himself in his heart, saying, \u201cI shall have peace,\nthough I walk in the stubbornness of my heart,\u201d to destroy the moist with the dry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 29:20"}, "The LORD will not pardon him, but then the LORD\u2019s anger and his jealousy will smoke against that man, and all the curse\nthat is written in this book will fall on him, and the LORD will blot out his name from under the sky.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 29:21"}, "The LORD will set him apart for evil out of all the tribes of Israel, according to all the curses of the covenant written\nin this book of the law. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 29:22"}, "The generation to come\u2014your children who will rise up after you, and the foreigner who will come from a far land\u2014will\nsay, when they see the plagues of that land, and the sicknesses with which the LORD has made it sick,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 29:23"}, "that all of its land is sulphur, salt, and burning, that it is not sown, doesn\u2019t produce, nor does any grass grow in it,\nlike the overthrow of Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboiim, which the LORD overthrew in his anger, and in his wrath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 29:24"}, "Even all the nations will say, \u201cWhy has the LORD done this to this land? What does the heat of this great anger mean?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 29:25"}, "Then men will say, \u201cBecause they abandoned the covenant of the LORD, Allah of their fathers, which he made with them when\nhe brought them out of the land of Egypt, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 29:26"}, "and went and served other gods and worshipped them, gods that they didn\u2019t know and that he had not given to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 29:27"}, "Therefore the LORD\u2019s anger burnt against this land, to bring on it all the curses that are written in this book.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 29:28"}, "The LORD rooted them out of their land in anger, in wrath, and in great indignation, and thrust them into another land,\nas it is today.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 29:29"}, "The secret things belong to the LORD our Allah; but the things that are revealed belong to us and to our children\nforever, that we may do all the words of this law. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 30"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 30:1"}, "It shall happen, when all these things have come on you, the blessing and the curse, which I have set before you, and you\nshall call them to mind amongst all the nations where Allah your LORD has driven you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 30:2"}, "and return to Allah your LORD and obey his voice according to all that I command you today, you and your children, with\nall your heart and with all your soul, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 30:3"}, "that then Allah your LORD will release you from captivity, have compassion on you, and will return and gather you from all\nthe peoples where Allah your LORD has scattered you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 30:4"}, "If your outcasts are in the uttermost parts of the heavens, from there Allah your LORD will gather you, and from there he\nwill bring you back. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 30:5"}, "The LORD your Allah will bring you into the land which your fathers possessed, and you will possess it. He will do you\ngood, and increase your numbers more than your fathers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 30:6"}, "The LORD your Allah will circumcise your heart, and the heart of your offspring, to love Allah your LORD with all your\nheart and with all your soul, that you may live. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 30:7"}, "The LORD your Allah will put all these curses on your enemies and on those who hate you, who persecuted you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 30:8"}, "You shall return and obey the LORD\u2019s voice, and do all his commandments which I command you today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 30:9"}, "The LORD your Allah will make you prosperous in all the work of your hand, in the fruit of your body, in the fruit of your\nlivestock, and in the fruit of your ground, for good; for the LORD will again rejoice over you for good, as he rejoiced over\nyour fathers, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 30:10"}, "if you will obey Allah your LORD\u2019s voice, to keep his commandments and his statutes which are written in this book of the\nlaw; if you turn to Allah your LORD with all your heart and with all your soul.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 30:11"}, "For this commandment which I command you today is not too hard for you or too distant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 30:12"}, "It is not in heaven, that you should say, \u201cWho will go up for us to heaven, bring it to us, and proclaim it to us, that\nwe may do it?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 30:13"}, "Neither is it beyond the sea, that you should say, \u201cWho will go over the sea for us, bring it to us, and proclaim it to\nus, that we may do it?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 30:14"}, "But the word is very near to you, in your mouth and in your heart, that you may do it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 30:15"}, "Behold, I have set before you today life and prosperity, and death and evil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 30:16"}, "For I command you today to love Allah your LORD, to walk in his ways and to keep his commandments, his statutes, and his\nordinances, that you may live and multiply, and that Allah your LORD may bless you in the land where you go in to possess it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 30:17"}, "But if your heart turns away, and you will not hear, but are drawn away and worship other gods, and serve them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 30:18"}, "I declare to you today that you will surely perish. You will not prolong your days in the land where you pass over the\nJordan to go in to possess it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 30:19"}, "I call heaven and earth to witness against you today that I have set before you life and death, the blessing and the\ncurse. Therefore choose life, that you may live, you and your descendants,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 30:20"}, "to love Allah your LORD, to obey his voice, and to cling to him; for he is your life, and the length of your days, that\nyou may dwell in the land which the LORD swore to your fathers, to Ibrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub, to give them.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 31"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 31:1"}, "Musa went and spoke these words to all Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 31:2"}, "He said to them, \u201cI am one hundred and twenty years old today. I can no more go out and come in. The LORD has said to me,\n\u2018You shall not go over this Jordan.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 31:3"}, "The LORD your Allah himself will go over before you. He will destroy these nations from before you, and you shall\ndispossess them. Joshua will go over before you, as the LORD has spoken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 31:4"}, "The LORD will do to them as he did to Sihon and to Og, the kings of the Amorites, and to their land, when he destroyed\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 31:5"}, "The LORD will deliver them up before you, and you shall do to them according to all the commandment which I have commanded\nyou. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 31:6"}, "Be strong and courageous. Don\u2019t be afraid or scared of them; for Allah your LORD himself is who goes with you. He will not\nfail you nor forsake you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 31:7"}, "Musa called to Joshua, and said to him in the sight of all Israel, \u201cBe strong and courageous, for you shall go with this\npeople into the land which the LORD has sworn to their fathers to give them; and you shall cause them to inherit it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 31:8"}, "The LORD himself is who goes before you. He will be with you. He will not fail you nor forsake you. Don\u2019t be afraid. Don\u2019t\nbe discouraged.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 31:9"}, "Musa wrote this law and delivered it to the priests the sons of Levi, who bore the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant, and to all\nthe elders of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 31:10"}, "Musa commanded them, saying, \u201cAt the end of every seven years, in the set time of the year of release, in the feast of\nbooths, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 31:11"}, "when all Israel has come to appear before Allah your LORD in the place which he will choose, you shall read this law\nbefore all Israel in their hearing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 31:12"}, "Assemble the people, the men and the women and the little ones, and the foreigners who are within your gates, that they\nmay hear, learn, fear Allah your LORD, and observe to do all the words of this law,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 31:13"}, "and that their children, who have not known, may hear and learn to fear Allah your LORD, as long as you live in the land\nwhere you go over the Jordan to possess it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 31:14"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cBehold, your days approach that you must die. Call Joshua, and present yourselves in the Tent of\nMeeting, that I may commission him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Musa and Joshua went, and presented themselves in the Tent of Meeting.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 31:15"}, "The LORD appeared in the Tent in a pillar of cloud, and the pillar of cloud stood over the Tent\u2019s door.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 31:16"}, "The LORD said to Musa, \u201cBehold, you shall sleep with your fathers. This people will rise up and play the prostitute after\nthe strange gods of the land where they go to be amongst them, and will forsake me and break my covenant which I have made with\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 31:17"}, "Then my anger shall be kindled against them in that day, and I will forsake them, and I will hide my face from them, and\nthey shall be devoured, and many evils and troubles shall come on them; so that they will say in that day, \u2018Haven\u2019t these evils\ncome on us because our Allah is not amongst us?\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 31:18"}, "I will surely hide my face in that day for all the evil which they have done, in that they have turned to other gods.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 31:19"}, "\u201cNow therefore write this song for yourselves, and teach it to the children of Israel. Put it in their mouths, that this\nsong may be a witness for me against the children of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 31:20"}, "For when I have brought them into the land which I swore to their fathers, flowing with milk and honey, and they have\neaten and filled themselves, and grown fat, then they will turn to other gods, and serve them, and despise me, and break my\ncovenant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 31:21"}, "It will happen, when many evils and troubles have come on them, that this song will testify before them as a witness; for\nit will not be forgotten out of the mouths of their descendants; for I know their ways and what they are doing today, before I\nhave brought them into the land which I promised them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 31:22"}, "So Musa wrote this song the same day, and taught it to the children of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 31:23"}, "He commissioned Joshua the son of Nun, and said, \u201cBe strong and courageous; for you shall bring the children of Israel\ninto the land which I swore to them. I will be with you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 31:24"}, "When Musa had finished writing the words of this law in a book, until they were finished,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 31:25"}, "Musa commanded the Levites, who bore the ark of the LORD\u2019s covenant, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 31:26"}, "\u201cTake this book of the law, and put it by the side of the ark of Allah your LORD\u2019s covenant, that it may be there for a\nwitness against you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 31:27"}, "For I know your rebellion and your stiff neck. Behold, while I am yet alive with you today, you have been rebellious\nagainst the LORD. How much more after my death? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 31:28"}, "Assemble to me all the elders of your tribes and your officers, that I may speak these words in their ears, and call\nheaven and earth to witness against them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 31:29"}, "For I know that after my death you will utterly corrupt yourselves, and turn away from the way which I have commanded\nyou; and evil will happen to you in the latter days, because you will do that which is evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, to provoke him\nto anger through the work of your hands.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 31:30"}, "Musa spoke in the ears of all the assembly of Israel the words of this song, until they were finished.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 32"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 32:1"}, "Give ear, you heavens, and I will speak. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let the earth hear the words of my mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 32:2"}, "My doctrine will drop as the rain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My speech will condense as the dew, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as the misty rain on the tender grass, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as the showers on the herb. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 32:3"}, "For I will proclaim the LORD\u2019s name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Ascribe greatness to our Allah! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 32:4"}, "The Rock: his work is perfect, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for all his ways are just. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A Allah of faithfulness who does no wrong, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["just and right is he. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 32:5"}, "They have dealt corruptly with him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are not his children, because of their defect. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are a perverse and crooked generation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 32:6"}, "Is this the way you repay the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["foolish and unwise people? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Isn\u2019t he your father who has bought you? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has made you and established you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 32:7"}, "Remember the days of old. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Consider the years of many generations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Ask your father, and he will show you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your elders, and they will tell you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 32:8"}, "When the Most High gave to the nations their inheritance, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when he separated the children of men, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["he set the bounds of the peoples \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["according to the number of the children of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 32:9"}, "For the LORD\u2019s portion is his people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yaqub is the lot of his inheritance. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 32:10"}, "He found him in a desert land, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in the waste howling wilderness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He surrounded him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He cared for him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He kept him as the apple of his eye. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 32:11"}, "As an eagle that stirs up her nest, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that flutters over her young, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["he spread abroad his wings, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he took them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he bore them on his feathers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 32:12"}, "The LORD alone led him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There was no foreign god with him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 32:13"}, "He made him ride on the high places of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He ate the increase of the field. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He caused him to suck honey out of the rock, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["oil out of the flinty rock; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 32:14"}, "butter from the herd, and milk from the flock, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with fat of lambs, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["rams of the breed of Bashan, and goats, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with the finest of the wheat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From the blood of the grape, you drank wine. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 32:15"}, "But Jeshurun grew fat, and kicked. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have grown fat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have grown thick. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have become sleek. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Then he abandoned Allah who made him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rejected the Rock of his salvation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 32:16"}, "They moved him to jealousy with strange gods. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They provoked him to anger with abominations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 32:17"}, "They sacrificed to demons, not Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to gods that they didn\u2019t know, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to new gods that came up recently, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which your fathers didn\u2019t dread. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 32:18"}, "Of the Rock who became your father, you are unmindful, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have forgotten Allah who gave you birth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 32:19"}, "The LORD saw and abhorred, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because of the provocation of his sons and his daughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 32:20"}, "He said, \u201cI will hide my face from them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will see what their end will be; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for they are a very perverse generation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["children in whom is no faithfulness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 32:21"}, "They have moved me to jealousy with that which is not Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They have provoked me to anger with their vanities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will move them to jealousy with those who are not a people.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will provoke them to anger with a foolish nation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 32:22"}, "For a fire is kindled in my anger, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that burns to the lowest Sheol,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["32:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["devours the earth with its increase, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and sets the foundations of the mountains on fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 32:23"}, "\u201cI will heap evils on them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will spend my arrows on them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 32:24"}, "They shall be wasted with hunger, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and devoured with burning heat \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and bitter destruction. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will send the teeth of animals on them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with the venom of vipers that glide in the dust. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 32:25"}, "Outside the sword will bereave, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and in the rooms, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["terror on both young man and virgin, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the nursing infant with the grey-haired man. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 32:26"}, "I said that I would scatter them afar. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I would make their memory to cease from amongst men; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 32:27"}, "were it not that I feared the provocation of the enemy, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lest their adversaries should judge wrongly, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lest they should say, \u2018Our hand is exalted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD has not done all this.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 32:28"}, "For they are a nation void of counsel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no understanding in them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 32:29"}, "Oh that they were wise, that they understood this, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that they would consider their latter end! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "DEU 32:30"}, "How could one chase a thousand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and two put ten thousand to flight, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["unless their Rock had sold them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD had delivered them up? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "DEU 32:31"}, "For their rock is not as our Rock, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even our enemies themselves concede. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "DEU 32:32"}, "For their vine is of the vine of Sodom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["of the fields of Gomorrah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their grapes are poison grapes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their clusters are bitter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 32:33"}, "Their wine is the poison of serpents, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the cruel venom of asps. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "DEU 32:34"}, "\u201cIsn\u2019t this laid up in store with me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["sealed up amongst my treasures? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "DEU 32:35"}, "Vengeance is mine, and recompense, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["at the time when their foot slides; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the day of their calamity is at hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their doom rushes at them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "DEU 32:36"}, "For the LORD will judge his people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have compassion on his servants, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["when he sees that their power is gone; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that there is no one remaining, shut up or left at large. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "DEU 32:37"}, "He will say, \u201cWhere are their gods, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the rock in which they took refuge; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "DEU 32:38"}, "which ate the fat of their sacrifices, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and drank the wine of their drink offering? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let them rise up and help you! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let them be your protection. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "DEU 32:39"}, "\u201cSee now that I myself am he. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no god with me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I kill and I make alive. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I wound and I heal. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no one who can deliver out of my hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "DEU 32:40"}, "For I lift up my hand to heaven and declare, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as I live forever, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "DEU 32:41"}, "if I sharpen my glittering sword, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my hand grasps it in judgement; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will take vengeance on my adversaries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will repay those who hate me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "DEU 32:42"}, "I will make my arrows drunk with blood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My sword shall devour flesh with the blood of the slain and the captives,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from the head of the leaders of the enemy.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "DEU 32:43"}, "Rejoice, you nations, with his people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for he will avenge the blood of his servants. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will take vengeance on his adversaries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will make atonement for his land and for his people.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["32:43 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["For this verse, LXX reads: Rejoice, you heavens, with him, and let all the angels of Allah worship him; rejoice\nyou Gentiles, with his people, and let all the sons of Allah strengthen themselves in him; for he will avenge the blood of his\nsons, and he will render vengeance, and recompense justice to his enemies, and will reward them that hate him; and the Lord\nshall purge the land of his people."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "DEU 32:44"}, "Musa came and spoke all the words of this song in the ears of the people, he and Joshua the son of Nun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "DEU 32:45"}, "Musa finished reciting all these words to all Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "DEU 32:46"}, "He said to them, \u201cSet your heart to all the words which I testify to you today, which you shall command your children to\nobserve to do, all the words of this law. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "DEU 32:47"}, "For it is no vain thing for you, because it is your life, and through this thing you shall prolong your days in the land,\nwhere you go over the Jordan to possess it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "DEU 32:48"}, "The LORD spoke to Musa that same day, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "DEU 32:49"}, "\u201cGo up into this mountain of Abarim, to Mount Nebo, which is in the land of Moab, that is across from Jericho; and see\nthe land of Canaan, which I give to the children of Israel for a possession.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "DEU 32:50"}, "Die on the mountain where you go up, and be gathered to your people, as Harun your brother died on Mount Hor, and was\ngathered to his people; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "DEU 32:51"}, "because you trespassed against me amongst the children of Israel at the waters of Meribah of Kadesh, in the wilderness of\nZin; because you didn\u2019t uphold my holiness amongst the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "DEU 32:52"}, "For you shall see the land from a distance; but you shall not go there into the land which I give the children of\nIsrael.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "33", "sid": "DEU 33"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 33:1"}, "This is the blessing with which Musa the man of Allah blessed the children of Israel before his death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 33:2"}, "He said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe LORD came from Sinai, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rose from Seir to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He shone from Mount Paran. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He came from the ten thousands of holy ones. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["At his right hand was a fiery law for them.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["33:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["another manuscript reads \u201cHe came with myriads of holy ones\nfrom the south, from his mountain slopes.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 33:3"}, "Yes, he loves the people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["All his saints are in your hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They sat down at your feet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Each receives your words. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 33:4"}, "Musa commanded us a law, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["an inheritance for the assembly of Yaqub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 33:5"}, "He was king in Jeshurun, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when the heads of the people were gathered, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["all the tribes of Israel together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 33:6"}, "\u201cLet Reuben live, and not die; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Nor let his men be few.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 33:7"}, "This is for Judah. He said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHear, LORD, the voice of Judah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Bring him in to his people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["With his hands he contended for himself. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You shall be a help against his adversaries.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 33:8"}, "About Levi he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cYour Thummim and your Urim are with your godly one, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["whom you proved at Massah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with whom you contended at the waters of Meribah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 33:9"}, "He said of his father, and of his mother, \u2018I have not seen him.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He didn\u2019t acknowledge his brothers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor did he know his own children; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for they have observed your word, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and keep your covenant. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 33:10"}, "They shall teach Yaqub your ordinances, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel your law. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They shall put incense before you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and whole burnt offering on your altar. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 33:11"}, "LORD, bless his skills. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Accept the work of his hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Strike through the hips of those who rise up against him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["of those who hate him, that they not rise again.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 33:12"}, "About Benjamin he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe beloved of the LORD will dwell in safety by him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He covers him all day long. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He dwells between his shoulders.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "DEU 33:13"}, "About Yusuf he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHis land is blessed by the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the precious things of the heavens, for the dew, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the deep that couches beneath, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "DEU 33:14"}, "for the precious things of the fruits of the sun, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the precious things that the moon can yield, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "DEU 33:15"}, "for the best things of the ancient mountains, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the precious things of the everlasting hills, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "DEU 33:16"}, "for the precious things of the earth and its fullness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the good will of him who lived in the bush.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["33:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["i.e., the burning bush of\nExodus 3:3-4."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let this come on the head of Yusuf, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["on the crown of the head of him who was separated from his brothers.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "DEU 33:17"}, "Majesty belongs to the firstborn of his herd. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His horns are the horns of the wild ox. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["With them he will push all the peoples to the ends of the earth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They are the ten thousands of Ephraim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are the thousands of Manasseh.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "DEU 33:18"}, "About Zebulun he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cRejoice, Zebulun, in your going out; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Issachar, in your tents. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "DEU 33:19"}, "They will call the peoples to the mountain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There they will offer sacrifices of righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for they will draw out the abundance of the seas, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the hidden treasures of the sand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "DEU 33:20"}, "About Gad he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHe who enlarges Gad is blessed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He dwells as a lioness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and tears the arm and the crown of the head. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "DEU 33:21"}, "He provided the first part for himself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the lawgiver\u2019s portion reserved was reserved for him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He came with the heads of the people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He executed the righteousness of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His ordinances with Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "DEU 33:22"}, "About Dan he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cDan is a lion\u2019s cub \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that leaps out of Bashan.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "DEU 33:23"}, "About Naphtali he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cNaphtali, satisfied with favour, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["full of the LORD\u2019s blessing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Possess the west and the south.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "DEU 33:24"}, "About Asher he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAsher is blessed with children. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let him be acceptable to his brothers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let him dip his foot in oil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "DEU 33:25"}, "Your bars will be iron and bronze. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["As your days, so your strength will be. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "DEU 33:26"}, "\u201cThere is no one like Allah, Jeshurun, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who rides on the heavens for your help, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in his excellency on the skies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "DEU 33:27"}, "The eternal Allah is your dwelling place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Underneath are the everlasting arms. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He thrust out the enemy from before you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and said, \u2018Destroy!\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "DEU 33:28"}, "Israel dwells in safety, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the fountain of Yaqub alone, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["In a land of grain and new wine. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, his heavens drop down dew. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "DEU 33:29"}, "You are happy, Israel! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who is like you, a people saved by the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the shield of your help, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the sword of your excellency? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Your enemies will submit themselves to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will tread on their high places.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "34", "sid": "DEU 34"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "DEU 34:1"}, "Musa went up from the plains of Moab to Mount Nebo, to the top of Pisgah, that is opposite Jericho. The LORD showed him\nall the land of Gilead to Dan, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "DEU 34:2"}, "and all Naphtali, and the land of Ephraim and Manasseh, and all the land of Judah, to the Western Sea,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "DEU 34:3"}, "and the south,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["34:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Negev"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and the Plain of the valley of Jericho the city of palm trees, to Zoar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "DEU 34:4"}, "The LORD said to him, \u201cThis is the land which I swore to Ibrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub, saying, \u2018I will give it to your\noffspring.\u2019 I have caused you to see it with your eyes, but you shall not go over there.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "DEU 34:5"}, "So Musa the servant of the LORD died there in the land of Moab, according to the LORD\u2019s word.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "DEU 34:6"}, "He buried him in the valley in the land of Moab opposite Beth Peor, but no man knows where his tomb is to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "DEU 34:7"}, "Musa was one hundred and twenty years old when he died. His eye was not dim, nor his strength gone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "DEU 34:8"}, "The children of Israel wept for Musa in the plains of Moab thirty days, until the days of weeping in the mourning for Musa\nwere ended. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "DEU 34:9"}, "Joshua the son of Nun was full of the spirit of wisdom, for Musa had laid his hands on him. The children of Israel\nlistened to him, and did as the LORD commanded Musa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "DEU 34:10"}, "Since then, there has not arisen a prophet in Israel like Musa, whom the LORD knew face to face,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "DEU 34:11"}, "in all the signs and the wonders which the LORD sent him to do in the land of Egypt, to Pharaoh, and to all his servants,\nand to all his land, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "DEU 34:12"}, "and in all the mighty hand, and in all the awesome deeds, which Musa did in the sight of all Israel.\n"]}]}